WEBVTT

1
00:00:58.680 --> 00:00:59.680
It's them!

2
00:01:01.800 --> 00:01:02.800
Get ready.

3
00:01:04.160 --> 00:01:05.680
Two more prisoners coming in!

4
00:01:07.120 --> 00:01:08.760
Prepare for docking!

5
00:01:10.320 --> 00:01:11.640
In position!

6
00:01:13.480 --> 00:01:14.520
Easy!

7
00:01:23.480 --> 00:01:24.960
Gate secure!

8
00:01:42.800 --> 00:01:44.440
Prisoner walking!

9
00:01:49.600 --> 00:01:50.800
Ready the cell!

10
00:02:09.880 --> 00:02:12.160
Oh, great. Another cellmate.

11
00:02:13.160 --> 00:02:14.760
No offense, pal. You seem lovely.

12
00:02:16.600 --> 00:02:18.800
Let's show you around.
Get you situated here.

13
00:02:19.280 --> 00:02:23.000
This is the bucket
where our pee freezes. And...

14
00:02:23.920 --> 00:02:24.920
Yeah, that's it.

15
00:02:25.280 --> 00:02:26.520
What's your name, lass?

16
00:02:26.600 --> 00:02:28.280
That's Holga. I'm Edgin.

17
00:02:28.360 --> 00:02:29.360
And you are?

18
00:02:29.440 --> 00:02:33.680
I've been in a lot of cells.
Never shared one with a female.

19
00:02:34.160 --> 00:02:35.520
Think I'm gonna like it.

20
00:02:35.600 --> 00:02:36.680
Word of advice

21
00:02:37.040 --> 00:02:39.920
Holga doesn't love to be disturbed
while she's eating her potatoes.

22
00:02:40.000 --> 00:02:41.600
Kind of the highlight of her day.

23
00:02:41.680 --> 00:02:42.680
Shut up, you!

24
00:02:43.240 --> 00:02:44.600
Sure thing. Have at it.

25
00:02:45.080 --> 00:02:47.120
Little shy, eh?

26
00:02:47.200 --> 00:02:49.920
I'm not so bad
once you get to know me.

27
00:02:52.360 --> 00:02:53.920
Don't be like that.

28
00:02:54.880 --> 00:02:57.360
We could be very happy to...

29
00:03:03.400 --> 00:03:06.280
I think I'm gonna do this
without fingers and make it a mitten.

30
00:03:07.000 --> 00:03:08.200
Who am I trying to impress?

31
00:03:09.600 --> 00:03:12.720
<i>Not fortune found, nor fate divine</i>

32
00:03:12.800 --> 00:03:16.200
<i>Come close to toping
the juice of the vine</i>

33
00:03:16.480 --> 00:03:18.480
<i>With cherry crew, we sip and sway</i>

34
00:03:18.560 --> 00:03:20.920
<i>Let's tip the tankard
and waste the day</i>

35
00:03:21.480 --> 00:03:22.840
Stop that singing!

36
00:03:23.480 --> 00:03:24.680
You got it, Tobias.

37
00:03:26.400 --> 00:03:28.200
The Absolution Council is tomorrow.

38
00:03:29.160 --> 00:03:30.600
Don't get your hopes up, Ed.

39
00:03:30.800 --> 00:03:31.960
What are you talking about?

40
00:03:32.040 --> 00:03:35.120
Jarnathan is on the council
this time. He's an Aarakocra.

41
00:03:35.480 --> 00:03:36.960
If anyone's gonna free us, it's him.

42
00:03:37.520 --> 00:03:38.680
Not gonna happen.

43
00:03:39.120 --> 00:03:42.360
I tell you, Holga,
this is your last day chopping ice.

44
00:03:46.640 --> 00:03:48.920
By authority of the Lords' Alliance

45
00:03:49.160 --> 00:03:52.480
this Absolution Council
will now come to order

46
00:03:52.560 --> 00:03:57.400
in the case of Edgin Darvis
and Holga Kilgore.

47
00:03:58.160 --> 00:04:01.160
This is the second year
of incarceration

48
00:04:01.240 --> 00:04:05.280
for the crimes of grand larceny
and skullduggery.

49
00:04:05.360 --> 00:04:07.200
It is the task of this council

50
00:04:07.280 --> 00:04:10.360
to determine your eligibility
for pardon.

51
00:04:10.440 --> 00:04:11.560
What say you?

52
00:04:11.920 --> 00:04:15.600
Thank you, Chancellor Anderton,
esteemed members of the council.

53
00:04:16.520 --> 00:04:21.320
Before I begin, I notice that
Chancellor Jarnathan is not present.

54
00:04:21.400 --> 00:04:22.960
Should we perhaps wait?

55
00:04:23.160 --> 00:04:25.200
Chancellor Jarnathan
was delayed by the storm.

56
00:04:25.280 --> 00:04:26.280
You may begin.

57
00:04:26.360 --> 00:04:27.600
I see. It's just that I-...

58
00:04:27.680 --> 00:04:31.200
we were really counting
on him to attend.

59
00:04:31.360 --> 00:04:33.640
Begin or waive your statement.

60
00:04:33.920 --> 00:04:34.960
Very well.

61
00:04:37.240 --> 00:04:39.520
I should start
by giving you some context.

62
00:04:40.560 --> 00:04:42.920
You may be surprised to learn
I wasn't always a thief.

63
00:04:43.360 --> 00:04:46.480
<i>Years ago, I became a member
of the Harpers faction</i>

64
00:04:46.560 --> 00:04:49.680
<i>a network of spies
who swear an oath to fight tyranny</i>

65
00:04:49.760 --> 00:04:52.960
<i>defend the oppressed
and to ask nothing in return.</i>

66
00:04:53.040 --> 00:04:56.840
<i>My wife, Zia, supported my decision,
even though she knew the risks.</i>

67
00:04:58.880 --> 00:05:01.240
<i>By day, I'd eavesdrop on mercenaries</i>

68
00:05:02.600 --> 00:05:04.520
<i>stop bandits in their tracks...</i>

69
00:05:07.600 --> 00:05:10.440
<i>and even bring Thayan Red Wizards
to justice.</i>

70
00:05:13.760 --> 00:05:17.360
<i>By night, I'd come home to
my loving wife, and daughter, Kira.</i>

71
00:05:18.480 --> 00:05:21.200
<i>To be honest, there were times
when I began to question</i>

72
00:05:21.280 --> 00:05:24.320
<i>the "asking nothing in return"
part of my oath.</i>

73
00:05:25.160 --> 00:05:26.720
<i>But my wife would always say</i>

74
00:05:26.800 --> 00:05:28.280
<i>"You don't have to give us everything</i>

75
00:05:28.320 --> 00:05:29.600
<i>you only have to give us you."</i>

76
00:05:29.680 --> 00:05:30.976
So what's the latest on Jarnathan?

77
00:05:31.000 --> 00:05:32.440
Is he close by? Because I can wait.

78
00:05:32.520 --> 00:05:34.080
Did you not hear what we said?

79
00:05:34.160 --> 00:05:36.880
Right, the storm. It's just that
based on what I know about Jarnathan

80
00:05:36.960 --> 00:05:39.360
I think he'd be especially
receptive to my story.

81
00:05:39.440 --> 00:05:41.696
And I'd hate to have to wait a whole
other year to come back in here

82
00:05:41.720 --> 00:05:42.800
- and...
- Proceed.

83
00:05:43.720 --> 00:05:44.960
Absolutely. Here we go.

84
00:05:45.480 --> 00:05:48.200
<i>When you're a Harper,
you're bound to make enemies.</i>

85
00:05:48.760 --> 00:05:51.880
<i>And sometimes those enemies
come looking for revenge.</i>

86
00:06:39.920 --> 00:06:43.320
<i>No cleric can repair the damage
from a Red Wizard's blade.</i>

87
00:06:43.720 --> 00:06:45.400
<i>There was no way to revive her.</i>

88
00:06:46.320 --> 00:06:50.360
<i>When Zia died,
so did my devotion to my oath.</i>

89
00:07:08.080 --> 00:07:11.360
I'm sorry, it's just
hard to relive this...

90
00:07:12.880 --> 00:07:14.440
without Jarnathan here.

91
00:07:14.520 --> 00:07:15.520
Again with this?

92
00:07:15.600 --> 00:07:17.656
But he missed the most important part
of my backstory!

93
00:07:17.680 --> 00:07:19.840
How can he judge me
without knowing my motivation?

94
00:07:19.920 --> 00:07:23.560
We are entirely capable of deciding
your case without Jarnathan.

95
00:07:23.640 --> 00:07:25.440
- Get on with it!
- Fine. Where was I?

96
00:07:26.320 --> 00:07:29.560
<i>By night, I'd come home to
my loving wife, and daughter Kira.</i>

97
00:07:29.640 --> 00:07:31.400
You went back too far. Stop stalling!

98
00:07:31.480 --> 00:07:33.920
Right, sorry. Yeah, broad strokes.

99
00:07:34.280 --> 00:07:38.240
<i>The next few months
were among my most shameful.</i>

100
00:07:41.160 --> 00:07:42.480
<i>That's when I met Holga.</i>

101
00:07:43.080 --> 00:07:44.280
<i>She took pity on me.</i>

102
00:07:45.520 --> 00:07:47.480
<i>Well, she took pity on the baby.</i>

103
00:07:48.320 --> 00:07:50.640
<i>Holga was a fellow resident
of rock bottom.</i>

104
00:07:51.560 --> 00:07:54.360
<i>Many years before,
she'd been cast out of her tribe</i>

105
00:07:54.440 --> 00:07:56.400
<i>for falling in love with an outsider.</i>

106
00:08:00.400 --> 00:08:02.760
<i>We quickly became
like brother and sister.</i>

107
00:08:02.840 --> 00:08:06.240
<i>With a relationship built
on trust and mutual respect.</i>

108
00:08:09.360 --> 00:08:11.800
<i>Neither of us had money
or an honest way to earn it</i>

109
00:08:11.880 --> 00:08:15.920
<i>so we decided to table "honest"
and we tried something new.</i>

110
00:08:17.000 --> 00:08:19.120
<i>It's intoxicating when you realize</i>

111
00:08:19.200 --> 00:08:22.640
<i>that what separates you
from what you've always wanted</i>

112
00:08:22.720 --> 00:08:25.560
<i>can be as thin as a pane of glass.</i>

113
00:08:39.240 --> 00:08:42.000
<i>You may be wondering how we could
carry on this criminal lifestyle</i>

114
00:08:42.080 --> 00:08:43.320
<i>with a young girl at home.</i>

115
00:08:44.040 --> 00:08:45.680
<i>Well, we didn't leave her at home.</i>

116
00:08:46.400 --> 00:08:47.760
- Come on, come on.
- Hurry, hurry!

117
00:08:47.800 --> 00:08:49.880
- Oi! Halt!
- Run, run, run!

118
00:08:50.320 --> 00:08:54.480
<i>Kira wasn't the only new recruit.
We also added Simon, a so-so sorcerer</i>

119
00:08:54.560 --> 00:08:58.440
<i>and a con man named Forge,
who pushed us to aim even higher.</i>

120
00:09:02.480 --> 00:09:04.360
<i>Before long, we became a team.</i>

121
00:09:05.720 --> 00:09:09.640
<i>Yes, we were thieves, but I tried
to hold us to a certain standard.</i>

122
00:09:09.720 --> 00:09:11.040
<i>We never harmed anyone.</i>

123
00:09:11.120 --> 00:09:14.120
<i>And we only robbed from those
who would feel it the least.</i>

124
00:09:15.680 --> 00:09:19.560
<i>But everything changed
when we met the wizard Sofina.</i>

125
00:09:21.000 --> 00:09:22.320
<i>We knew almost nothing about her.</i>

126
00:09:22.360 --> 00:09:25.640
<i>Only that she wanted our help
in robbing Korinn's Keep.</i>

127
00:09:25.720 --> 00:09:27.816
<i>That's a Harper stronghold.
I don't know if you've heard of it.</i>

128
00:09:27.840 --> 00:09:29.680
<i>I'm sure Jarnathan has.</i>

129
00:09:30.640 --> 00:09:32.560
<i>The keep was filled
with the priceless relics</i>

130
00:09:32.640 --> 00:09:33.680
<i>seized from evildoers</i>

131
00:09:33.760 --> 00:09:36.320
<i>and only Harpers could
gain access to the vault.</i>

132
00:09:36.400 --> 00:09:38.240
<i>Which is why Sofina came to us.</i>

133
00:09:38.640 --> 00:09:41.160
<i>At first, I refused.
I wouldn't stoop that low.</i>

134
00:09:41.800 --> 00:09:44.400
<i>But then Forge told me that
among the relics in Korinn's Keep</i>

135
00:09:44.480 --> 00:09:46.840
<i>there was a Tablet of Reawakening</i>

136
00:09:46.920 --> 00:09:49.760
<i>capable of bringing back
a single deceased person.</i>

137
00:09:50.200 --> 00:09:52.480
<i>Even one killed
by a Red Wizard's blade.</i>

138
00:09:53.000 --> 00:09:55.040
<i>You can probably see
where this is going.</i>

139
00:09:55.400 --> 00:09:56.400
Why can't I come?

140
00:09:56.480 --> 00:09:58.400
Sorry, Kir, this one's too dangerous.

141
00:09:58.640 --> 00:10:00.080
Then you shouldn't go.

142
00:10:00.760 --> 00:10:02.520
We have everything that we need.

143
00:10:02.600 --> 00:10:05.400
Not yet. But this is the last one.

144
00:10:06.480 --> 00:10:07.480
Trust me.

145
00:10:12.400 --> 00:10:14.400
Chin up, Bug. We'll be right back.

146
00:10:14.720 --> 00:10:16.056
I didn't tell her about the tablet.

147
00:10:16.080 --> 00:10:17.696
It would break her heart
if it all went to shit.

148
00:10:17.720 --> 00:10:19.000
And, well

149
00:10:19.800 --> 00:10:21.040
to shit it went.

150
00:10:50.840 --> 00:10:51.960
See you soon, love.

151
00:11:03.320 --> 00:11:04.360
Intruders!

152
00:11:05.680 --> 00:11:06.680
There they are!

153
00:11:11.520 --> 00:11:12.760
We don't hurt anyone.

154
00:11:28.600 --> 00:11:30.200
She's caught in the Time Stop!

155
00:11:30.400 --> 00:11:32.920
- Counter it, Simon!
- I can't. Sofina's too powerful.

156
00:11:42.880 --> 00:11:45.440
Take the tablet. Keep Kira safe.

157
00:11:49.920 --> 00:11:51.200
You have my word.

158
00:12:01.400 --> 00:12:03.960
The truth is, even if
this council were to sentence me

159
00:12:04.040 --> 00:12:06.680
to another two years
or twenty for that matter

160
00:12:07.760 --> 00:12:09.136
it would never be punishment enough

161
00:12:09.160 --> 00:12:11.520
for the worst crime
I ever committed...

162
00:12:14.040 --> 00:12:15.880
robbing my daughter of her father.

163
00:12:16.400 --> 00:12:19.400
But know that,
if you do choose to free me

164
00:12:20.120 --> 00:12:22.880
I'll spend the rest of my days
trying to right that wrong.

165
00:12:24.640 --> 00:12:25.640
Anything you want to add?

166
00:12:26.200 --> 00:12:27.200
I'm good.

167
00:12:33.080 --> 00:12:37.440
Before you announce your decision,
I implore you to please wait for...

168
00:12:39.560 --> 00:12:41.000
- Jarnathan!
- Pardon my belatedness.

169
00:12:41.080 --> 00:12:43.680
I can't tell you
how happy I am to see you!

170
00:12:43.760 --> 00:12:44.760
Holga, now!

171
00:12:45.040 --> 00:12:46.080
Guards!

172
00:12:46.640 --> 00:12:47.880
Release me, sir!

173
00:12:48.320 --> 00:12:50.000
She's throwing potatoes!

174
00:12:51.040 --> 00:12:52.400
Oh, Jarnathan!

175
00:12:54.000 --> 00:12:55.600
But we approved your pardon!

176
00:13:09.000 --> 00:13:10.800
Fly, bird, fly!

177
00:13:33.400 --> 00:13:34.680
He's still breathing.

178
00:13:37.640 --> 00:13:39.200
I told you he'd get us out!

179
00:14:43.240 --> 00:14:44.360
Any sign of Kira?

180
00:14:45.840 --> 00:14:47.200
Been empty for a while.

181
00:15:03.240 --> 00:15:04.720
Where do you think Forge took her?

182
00:15:04.800 --> 00:15:06.600
I can't see him leaving
the Sword Coast.

183
00:15:06.680 --> 00:15:07.960
Forge always liked cities.

184
00:15:09.600 --> 00:15:11.320
Some supper for you and your wife?

185
00:15:11.840 --> 00:15:13.880
- What? No. She's not my wife.
- Me with that?

186
00:15:13.960 --> 00:15:16.200
- With those lips?
- That's so gross. Just the drinks.

187
00:15:18.800 --> 00:15:21.120
So, we take a boat down
to Baldur's Gate

188
00:15:21.800 --> 00:15:23.080
and then head north.

189
00:15:23.520 --> 00:15:26.880
And while we're looking for Forge,
I'll pay Marlamin a visit.

190
00:15:28.560 --> 00:15:30.456
You sure you really want
to put yourself through that?

191
00:15:30.480 --> 00:15:32.080
What if he doesn't want
to talk to you?

192
00:15:32.320 --> 00:15:34.400
- It's not about what he wants.
- Okay.

193
00:15:34.800 --> 00:15:35.800
It's about closure.

194
00:15:36.080 --> 00:15:38.256
He sent you a letter saying
he wasn't your husband anymore.

195
00:15:38.280 --> 00:15:40.280
Wasn't that closure?

196
00:15:40.560 --> 00:15:42.000
- You wouldn't understand.
- I don't.

197
00:15:42.040 --> 00:15:43.920
I clearly, clearly don't.

198
00:15:49.000 --> 00:15:50.000
Is that...

199
00:15:51.280 --> 00:15:52.760
Son of a bitch.

200
00:15:53.120 --> 00:15:55.640
Forge is Lord of Neverwinter.

201
00:15:56.120 --> 00:15:58.080
How did that clown pull that off?

202
00:15:59.200 --> 00:16:00.960
Well, as long as he's got Kira,
I don't care.

203
00:16:01.000 --> 00:16:02.680
Come on. Let's go.

204
00:16:03.920 --> 00:16:05.760
Thanks, pal.
What's wrong with my lips?

205
00:16:06.000 --> 00:16:07.560
- They're too big for your face.
- What?

206
00:16:08.320 --> 00:16:09.480
A lot of people like my lips.

207
00:16:38.400 --> 00:16:40.000
I've never seen
this place so crowded.

208
00:16:40.640 --> 00:16:42.800
Must be coming in
for the High Sun Games.

209
00:16:43.320 --> 00:16:46.040
Yeah, my dad took me to the last one
before they were outlawed.

210
00:16:46.480 --> 00:16:47.480
Anyone win?

211
00:16:48.040 --> 00:16:50.160
Well, one contestant made it
to the final round

212
00:16:50.240 --> 00:16:52.560
before a monster ate
his upper body, so...

213
00:16:53.960 --> 00:16:54.960
no.

214
00:16:58.000 --> 00:17:00.680
It's nice to see that Forge
hasn't lost his sense of modesty.

215
00:17:06.640 --> 00:17:08.920
- How long has it been?
- Two years.

216
00:17:09.000 --> 00:17:10.880
No, how long
have we been waiting here?

217
00:17:13.480 --> 00:17:14.480
Dad.

218
00:17:15.440 --> 00:17:16.440
Holga?

219
00:17:16.760 --> 00:17:17.760
Kira.

220
00:17:22.880 --> 00:17:24.040
I missed you so much.

221
00:17:24.120 --> 00:17:25.200
Hello, Bug.

222
00:17:28.400 --> 00:17:29.520
- Come here.
- Hi.

223
00:17:33.480 --> 00:17:34.880
I thought about you every day.

224
00:17:39.520 --> 00:17:40.520
I made you these.

225
00:17:44.000 --> 00:17:46.000
- What are they?
- Mittens!

226
00:17:48.360 --> 00:17:49.360
Thanks.

227
00:17:49.960 --> 00:17:51.120
Have you been okay?

228
00:17:52.000 --> 00:17:54.000
Uncle Forge has been very good to me.

229
00:17:54.400 --> 00:17:56.120
"Uncle" Forge?

230
00:17:58.520 --> 00:18:00.360
Come on. He wants to see you.

231
00:18:02.320 --> 00:18:04.360
I still wear the pendant
you got me, Holga.

232
00:18:05.040 --> 00:18:07.800
I use it to sneak
around the castle sometimes.

233
00:18:09.720 --> 00:18:11.160
So strange that you're here.

234
00:18:11.240 --> 00:18:12.400
Hey, Kir, look.

235
00:18:14.400 --> 00:18:18.600
I want you to know I am so sorry
for how things turned out.

236
00:18:18.920 --> 00:18:19.920
I took a risk.

237
00:18:20.680 --> 00:18:21.880
And it didn't pay off.

238
00:18:22.400 --> 00:18:24.000
Why do you look mad at me?

239
00:18:25.640 --> 00:18:27.560
Because you're acting like
it wasn't your fault.

240
00:18:28.520 --> 00:18:30.120
There they are!

241
00:18:33.120 --> 00:18:34.600
Old friends.

242
00:18:34.920 --> 00:18:37.240
What a wonderful surprise. Come.

243
00:18:42.120 --> 00:18:44.960
Do I spy a little bit of gray?

244
00:18:45.120 --> 00:18:46.120
I do. I like it.

245
00:18:46.200 --> 00:18:48.640
It's scoundrelly but professorial.

246
00:18:48.720 --> 00:18:51.080
You look like a...
What do you look like?

247
00:18:51.160 --> 00:18:54.200
You look like
a well-read fisherman with secrets.

248
00:18:56.040 --> 00:18:57.320
And Holga.

249
00:18:58.320 --> 00:18:59.880
I know you don't like hugs.

250
00:19:00.480 --> 00:19:02.040
But I need one. Yes?

251
00:19:07.440 --> 00:19:10.080
These last years must have been
dreadful, yeah, but I tell you what

252
00:19:10.320 --> 00:19:11.760
I did think you'd serve longer.

253
00:19:11.960 --> 00:19:13.040
Oh, yeah...

254
00:19:13.120 --> 00:19:16.000
We... We got an... early release.

255
00:19:16.440 --> 00:19:18.520
- Good behavior.
- Yeah. Behaving, behaving good.

256
00:19:19.040 --> 00:19:20.040
I see.

257
00:19:20.280 --> 00:19:22.040
Well, welcome. Welcome back.

258
00:19:23.440 --> 00:19:25.680
That's blistering.
That's blisteringly hot.

259
00:19:25.920 --> 00:19:26.920
Yet again.

260
00:19:27.160 --> 00:19:29.056
Kira, we really should speak
to the kitchen staff

261
00:19:29.080 --> 00:19:31.960
because there's simply no need
for it to be this hot.

262
00:19:32.200 --> 00:19:33.376
Yeah, yeah, the-the tea's hot.

263
00:19:33.400 --> 00:19:35.440
So, how are you
the Lord of Neverwinter?

264
00:19:35.720 --> 00:19:36.720
Right.

265
00:19:36.800 --> 00:19:40.880
Before you went off to prison, you
charged me with Kira's well-being.

266
00:19:41.240 --> 00:19:42.680
Didn't think much of it at the time.

267
00:19:42.880 --> 00:19:45.640
But there came a moment
when I looked into her eyes

268
00:19:45.720 --> 00:19:48.120
and I suddenly knew
I had to be a better man.

269
00:19:48.200 --> 00:19:50.416
Obviously, I couldn't give back
the treasures we'd stolen

270
00:19:50.440 --> 00:19:52.800
so when Lord Neverember fell ill

271
00:19:52.880 --> 00:19:56.320
I seized the chance to try and,
you know, make a difference.

272
00:19:56.600 --> 00:19:59.056
And the money from Korinn's Keep
paved the way for my campaign.

273
00:19:59.080 --> 00:20:00.280
But I will tell you this

274
00:20:01.240 --> 00:20:02.400
couldn't have done it alone.

275
00:20:03.400 --> 00:20:04.760
And here she is!

276
00:20:05.120 --> 00:20:06.480
You remember Sofina.

277
00:20:07.000 --> 00:20:08.136
You're still working with her?

278
00:20:08.160 --> 00:20:09.720
She's the one that got us caught.

279
00:20:09.800 --> 00:20:13.000
Not true, no. Without her,
we all would have been caught.

280
00:20:13.080 --> 00:20:14.880
And since then, she has become...

281
00:20:15.480 --> 00:20:17.200
my top adviser.

282
00:20:19.440 --> 00:20:22.320
The tea is scorching, I do apologize.
It's scorching hot.

283
00:20:24.000 --> 00:20:25.000
Sofina.

284
00:20:26.240 --> 00:20:27.760
Would you mind very much...

285
00:20:28.720 --> 00:20:29.760
Certainly.

286
00:20:35.320 --> 00:20:36.320
Good. Thank you.

287
00:20:37.440 --> 00:20:40.520
I didn't realize you were gonna put
your finger in... in the cup, so...

288
00:20:41.680 --> 00:20:43.120
I'm gonna leave that for later.

289
00:20:43.200 --> 00:20:46.800
Well, if you'll give us the tablet,
Kira, Holga and I will be on our way.

290
00:20:47.680 --> 00:20:49.360
Of course that's why you came back.

291
00:20:50.360 --> 00:20:52.720
No, it wasn't for me.
It was for that Tablet of Riches.

292
00:20:53.200 --> 00:20:55.760
- Riches?
- No, it's...

293
00:20:55.840 --> 00:20:57.240
it's the Tablet of Reawakening.

294
00:20:57.440 --> 00:20:58.560
I'm sorry, what's this now?

295
00:20:58.880 --> 00:21:01.200
The reason why I agreed to the heist.

296
00:21:01.280 --> 00:21:04.040
Is that what he's told you?
That I left you for more riches?

297
00:21:04.120 --> 00:21:06.600
I told her the truth.
She has a right to know it.

298
00:21:07.920 --> 00:21:09.720
He's been lying to you, Kira.

299
00:21:10.000 --> 00:21:11.000
I wanted to...

300
00:21:11.320 --> 00:21:12.720
I wanted to bring your mother back.

301
00:21:13.200 --> 00:21:15.760
Ed, come on. Look, I know
how much you crave her forgiveness

302
00:21:15.840 --> 00:21:17.496
but I promise you,
more lies is not the way.

303
00:21:17.520 --> 00:21:18.880
You snake!

304
00:21:19.080 --> 00:21:21.200
You know damn well what he was after.

305
00:21:21.280 --> 00:21:23.440
Why wouldn't you tell me
if you were doing it for Mom?

306
00:21:24.040 --> 00:21:26.240
Because I didn't want you
to lose her again if I failed.

307
00:21:26.760 --> 00:21:29.360
But you can't blame the poor girl
for distrusting you.

308
00:21:30.080 --> 00:21:31.120
After all

309
00:21:32.360 --> 00:21:35.560
you have been lying since you set
foot in the room, haven't you?

310
00:21:40.800 --> 00:21:41.800
You escaped?

311
00:21:41.880 --> 00:21:43.560
We were trying
to get back to you, Bug.

312
00:21:43.640 --> 00:21:45.600
Kira, look at me, look at me.
I-I swear to you

313
00:21:45.680 --> 00:21:47.560
it was a Tablet of Reawakening.

314
00:21:47.920 --> 00:21:50.720
I was doing it for Mom,
for all of us. You have to trust me.

315
00:21:51.600 --> 00:21:53.760
You told me to trust you
when you left me.

316
00:21:56.880 --> 00:21:58.160
Kira, no, wait, wait!

317
00:21:58.240 --> 00:22:00.120
- Kira!
- Give her time, give her time.

318
00:22:00.320 --> 00:22:03.120
She's had years to resent you
for your absence.

319
00:22:03.360 --> 00:22:05.400
And you've had years
to poison her against me.

320
00:22:05.480 --> 00:22:06.920
No, that is not true.

321
00:22:07.840 --> 00:22:09.440
We very rarely spoke of you at all.

322
00:22:09.600 --> 00:22:11.360
Give him what he came for.

323
00:22:11.440 --> 00:22:14.680
The tablet?
I don't think I will be returning it.

324
00:22:15.480 --> 00:22:17.880
Or your daughter, for that matter.

325
00:22:18.120 --> 00:22:19.240
You bastard!

326
00:22:25.240 --> 00:22:27.600
And now you're in the floor!

327
00:22:27.920 --> 00:22:29.640
I hate to see that.

328
00:22:29.880 --> 00:22:33.400
Sofina really is
a very, very powerful wizard!

329
00:22:33.480 --> 00:22:34.856
You'd have thought that
you'd have learned that

330
00:22:34.880 --> 00:22:36.480
the last time she trapped you.

331
00:22:38.440 --> 00:22:40.240
You always wanted us to get caught.

332
00:22:40.320 --> 00:22:42.600
No, I wanted you and Simon
to get caught

333
00:22:42.680 --> 00:22:44.160
but he managed to escape somehow.

334
00:22:44.240 --> 00:22:48.200
All these years together, and
you double-cross us for this witch?

335
00:22:48.400 --> 00:22:50.520
Never put your trust in a con man.

336
00:22:50.600 --> 00:22:51.640
Save for this...

337
00:22:52.200 --> 00:22:54.960
Kira really is happy
and very well taken care of here,

338
00:22:55.040 --> 00:22:58.080
and I have truly come
to love her as my own.

339
00:22:58.160 --> 00:23:01.960
I never actually saw the appeal
of being a father till I became one.

340
00:23:02.040 --> 00:23:05.440
But to have another person
look up to you

341
00:23:05.520 --> 00:23:08.360
and allow you to shape them
in your own image.

342
00:23:08.440 --> 00:23:09.760
It's a bit like a god!

343
00:23:10.760 --> 00:23:14.720
Well, hang on, I'm a god and a lord.
I am really doing all right!

344
00:23:14.920 --> 00:23:15.920
Blackwood?

345
00:23:16.760 --> 00:23:18.480
Could you possibly
return them to prison?

346
00:23:18.560 --> 00:23:20.320
And be sure to collect the bounty.

347
00:23:20.600 --> 00:23:22.800
Well, I must away. I am expecting

348
00:23:22.880 --> 00:23:25.680
two of the wealthiest men
from Baldur's Gate and Waterdeep

349
00:23:25.760 --> 00:23:28.480
to talk about the High Sun Games,
which are back!

350
00:23:28.920 --> 00:23:30.400
So there's something, isn't it?

351
00:23:31.320 --> 00:23:33.560
It was genuinely lovely
to see you both.

352
00:23:36.320 --> 00:23:38.000
Holga! Holga! Holga!

353
00:23:40.720 --> 00:23:42.400
Kill both of them.

354
00:23:48.480 --> 00:23:49.696
We got to get her out of there.

355
00:23:49.720 --> 00:23:50.720
We will.

356
00:23:50.800 --> 00:23:52.920
But we need to think
of our own hides right now.

357
00:23:53.000 --> 00:23:54.840
Yeah, you got this, right?

358
00:23:54.920 --> 00:23:55.960
I know you don't.

359
00:23:56.040 --> 00:23:57.040
On your knees.

360
00:24:02.400 --> 00:24:03.560
Handsome blade.

361
00:24:04.400 --> 00:24:06.240
Is that the work
of Ghelryn Foehammer?

362
00:24:07.280 --> 00:24:08.280
How did you know?

363
00:24:08.520 --> 00:24:09.800
The inlay on the haft.

364
00:24:12.720 --> 00:24:15.000
How's the weight? Does it parry?

365
00:24:15.680 --> 00:24:16.800
It's darksteel.

366
00:24:17.760 --> 00:24:19.640
- Very nice.
- Now put your heads down.

367
00:24:21.240 --> 00:24:22.240
Wait!

368
00:24:22.640 --> 00:24:23.760
What do you clean it with?

369
00:24:25.560 --> 00:24:27.000
You're about to lose your head.

370
00:24:27.600 --> 00:24:29.040
This is what you're concerned with?

371
00:24:29.840 --> 00:24:31.040
If you wouldn't mind.

372
00:24:33.400 --> 00:24:36.680
Boiled linseed oil. Once a month.

373
00:24:36.760 --> 00:24:38.000
Should be once a week.

374
00:24:38.080 --> 00:24:39.720
That's why
you're getting rust on the bit.

375
00:24:40.800 --> 00:24:42.120
Okay, chop it off.

376
00:24:42.200 --> 00:24:43.280
Chop it off, let's do it.

377
00:24:51.440 --> 00:24:52.440
Get her!

378
00:25:04.720 --> 00:25:05.760
Stop her!

379
00:25:09.600 --> 00:25:10.880
We got 'em now!

380
00:25:37.640 --> 00:25:40.360
- Before we leave the city...
- Get boiled linseed oil, I know.

381
00:25:47.040 --> 00:25:48.040
Knock, knock.

382
00:25:49.800 --> 00:25:51.640
I wanted to make sure
you were all right.

383
00:25:54.960 --> 00:25:56.880
I knew I'd see him again one day.

384
00:25:59.280 --> 00:26:01.000
I just hoped it would be different.

385
00:26:01.800 --> 00:26:03.480
Well, you have to understand that

386
00:26:04.520 --> 00:26:06.120
when he lost your mother

387
00:26:07.280 --> 00:26:08.760
he sort of lost himself.

388
00:26:11.880 --> 00:26:13.560
Why did he lie about the tablet?

389
00:26:14.720 --> 00:26:18.120
Maybe he was ashamed to admit
how much he'd given up for so little.

390
00:26:21.800 --> 00:26:23.400
I should probably go speak to him.

391
00:26:26.280 --> 00:26:27.280
What?

392
00:26:27.680 --> 00:26:29.360
Well, he's gone, my dear. He's gone.

393
00:26:30.120 --> 00:26:32.200
I gave him
the Tablet of Riches and...

394
00:26:33.760 --> 00:26:34.760
he left.

395
00:26:39.440 --> 00:26:40.440
Holga, too?

396
00:26:42.400 --> 00:26:43.520
I'm sorry.

397
00:26:45.920 --> 00:26:48.680
And I want you to know
that even if he isn't there for you

398
00:26:49.440 --> 00:26:51.200
I always will be.

399
00:26:52.840 --> 00:26:53.840
I know.

400
00:26:55.000 --> 00:26:56.800
The fact that you see good in me

401
00:26:57.200 --> 00:27:00.000
makes me believe that
there might just be some in there.

402
00:27:00.800 --> 00:27:03.400
We could shoot an arrow
with a message into her room.

403
00:27:04.200 --> 00:27:05.200
What if it hits her?

404
00:27:05.280 --> 00:27:06.880
That's a risk
we're gonna have to take.

405
00:27:07.480 --> 00:27:09.200
Killing my daughter with an arrow?

406
00:27:09.560 --> 00:27:10.800
No, it's not.

407
00:27:11.400 --> 00:27:14.280
Even if she got the message,
she wouldn't come. She thinks of...

408
00:27:15.000 --> 00:27:16.760
Forge as her dad.

409
00:27:18.320 --> 00:27:21.000
We have to get into that castle
and take her out ourselves.

410
00:27:21.080 --> 00:27:22.320
That's crazy, Ed.

411
00:27:22.560 --> 00:27:24.200
Castle Never's tighter
than Korinn's Keep

412
00:27:24.280 --> 00:27:25.760
and you know what happened with that.

413
00:27:26.080 --> 00:27:27.640
We're gonna need a team.

414
00:27:28.120 --> 00:27:31.280
Team? Who's gonna help us out?
We have nothing to pay them with.

415
00:27:31.360 --> 00:27:33.120
Yeah, but Forge does.

416
00:27:33.400 --> 00:27:36.056
He said the richest people were
coming to bet on the High Sun Games.

417
00:27:36.080 --> 00:27:37.496
There'll be a fortune in that vault.

418
00:27:37.520 --> 00:27:40.000
Yeah. Not to mention the tablet.

419
00:27:40.640 --> 00:27:41.880
And then Kira will know that...

420
00:27:41.920 --> 00:27:44.000
We abandoned her
for the right reason.

421
00:27:45.400 --> 00:27:49.000
I wouldn't put it like that,
but... yeah. Yeah.

422
00:27:49.880 --> 00:27:51.360
Who do we get for this team?

423
00:27:51.920 --> 00:27:53.920
You know, I wonder
if Simon's still in Triboar.

424
00:27:54.160 --> 00:27:55.680
Simon's a terrible sorcerer.

425
00:27:56.200 --> 00:27:58.680
We haven't seen him in two years.
I'm sure he's gotten better.

426
00:27:59.840 --> 00:28:02.800
No one can hold a candle
to this trick.

427
00:28:07.400 --> 00:28:10.200
How about this one? You people like
the smell of fresh-cut grass?

428
00:28:14.360 --> 00:28:16.680
Smell that? It's fresh-cut grass.

429
00:28:16.760 --> 00:28:18.760
My five-year-old can do that magic.

430
00:28:18.840 --> 00:28:21.120
But can he do this?

431
00:28:24.280 --> 00:28:25.280
Boo.

432
00:28:25.680 --> 00:28:26.960
He hasn't gotten better.

433
00:28:27.040 --> 00:28:29.160
I don't think it's about
what he's doing up there.

434
00:28:29.240 --> 00:28:32.320
This is quite hard to be
slightly blurry like this, you know.

435
00:28:32.400 --> 00:28:34.840
Anyone can be very blurry,
but to be slightly blurry

436
00:28:34.920 --> 00:28:36.360
that's the real magic.

437
00:28:37.880 --> 00:28:38.880
Is that...

438
00:28:42.000 --> 00:28:43.200
- What was that?
- Where?

439
00:28:45.320 --> 00:28:46.320
Hey!

440
00:28:47.520 --> 00:28:49.320
He's nickin' our bits and bobs!

441
00:28:49.400 --> 00:28:51.760
That's... It's not what you think.
It's all part of the act.

442
00:28:51.920 --> 00:28:52.920
He's lying.

443
00:28:53.440 --> 00:28:54.440
Get him!

444
00:28:55.680 --> 00:28:56.680
Get him!

445
00:28:59.040 --> 00:29:00.280
Shield spell!

446
00:29:00.360 --> 00:29:01.520
Shield spell!

447
00:29:09.680 --> 00:29:11.120
That wasn't a shield spell.

448
00:29:26.600 --> 00:29:28.280
I am not loving this show.

449
00:29:31.600 --> 00:29:33.000
You're a dead man!

450
00:29:34.520 --> 00:29:35.560
<i>Obscrus mo...</i>

451
00:29:39.320 --> 00:29:40.320
<i>moyfin!</i>

452
00:29:44.120 --> 00:29:45.600
<i>Moyfin!</i> Damn!

453
00:29:45.680 --> 00:29:46.880
<i>Obscrus moyfin!</i>

454
00:29:51.520 --> 00:29:52.960
- Simon?
- Holga!

455
00:29:53.040 --> 00:29:54.040
Staying for an encore?

456
00:29:54.120 --> 00:29:55.200
Get me out of here.

457
00:30:06.800 --> 00:30:08.840
I could've warned you
Forge was a prick.

458
00:30:08.920 --> 00:30:10.896
Soon as we left that vault,
Sofina tried to kill me

459
00:30:10.920 --> 00:30:12.120
and he just stood by.

460
00:30:12.520 --> 00:30:14.960
You know, there's rumors
she made Lord Neverember fall ill

461
00:30:15.040 --> 00:30:16.400
to clear the way for Forge.

462
00:30:16.920 --> 00:30:18.360
Her magic is on a whole other level.

463
00:30:18.400 --> 00:30:20.640
Don't sell yourself short.
We saw your show.

464
00:30:20.880 --> 00:30:23.400
Yeah, you can hit her
with that fresh-cut grass trick.

465
00:30:23.640 --> 00:30:24.640
That's funny.

466
00:30:24.920 --> 00:30:27.040
Look, I don't blame you
for wanting to save Kira

467
00:30:27.120 --> 00:30:29.480
and I love the idea
of knocking Forge off his perch

468
00:30:29.560 --> 00:30:32.000
but robbing Castle Never
isn't worth the risk.

469
00:30:32.160 --> 00:30:33.600
And robbing your audience is?

470
00:30:35.480 --> 00:30:36.520
How broke are you?

471
00:30:36.760 --> 00:30:37.760
Desperately.

472
00:30:37.840 --> 00:30:39.736
I was planning
on sleeping in the theater tonight

473
00:30:39.760 --> 00:30:41.040
but now that seems imprudent.

474
00:30:41.240 --> 00:30:42.240
So?

475
00:30:42.320 --> 00:30:45.400
Do we even know what sort of
arcane magic is protecting the vault?

476
00:30:45.600 --> 00:30:46.800
- We're gonna find out!
- How?

477
00:30:46.880 --> 00:30:48.456
You gonna sneak past
the entire Castle Watch?

478
00:30:48.480 --> 00:30:49.480
Me? No.

479
00:30:49.560 --> 00:30:51.680
A druid maybe, a Wild Shape.

480
00:30:51.920 --> 00:30:54.160
They could get in and out
undetected as a...

481
00:30:54.760 --> 00:30:57.160
- as a mouse or a...
- A deer.

482
00:30:57.240 --> 00:31:00.400
Yes, a deer! It'll blend in with
all the other deer in the castle.

483
00:31:00.600 --> 00:31:01.600
Don't mock me.

484
00:31:02.000 --> 00:31:03.600
Where can we find a druid?

485
00:31:04.760 --> 00:31:06.920
I know a druid. Doric.

486
00:31:07.000 --> 00:31:08.920
She's truly one of a kind.

487
00:31:09.440 --> 00:31:11.360
Sounds romantic in nature.

488
00:31:11.440 --> 00:31:12.880
Yeah. For me it was.

489
00:31:13.600 --> 00:31:17.400
She, however, found my lack
of self-esteem unattractive.

490
00:31:17.480 --> 00:31:18.680
Not your best trait.

491
00:31:19.160 --> 00:31:20.160
Thank you.

492
00:31:22.760 --> 00:31:25.360
In the name of Forge Fitzwilliam

493
00:31:25.440 --> 00:31:29.560
the prisoner is hereby sentenced
to death by dismemberment

494
00:31:29.960 --> 00:31:33.680
for the crime
of speaking ill of our leader.

495
00:31:33.920 --> 00:31:36.320
The Emerald Enclave
will never relent!

496
00:31:36.640 --> 00:31:38.160
Justice cannot be killed!

497
00:31:38.240 --> 00:31:39.560
On my command.

498
00:31:39.880 --> 00:31:41.680
- Your Doric's a bit of a radical.
- Ready?

499
00:31:41.760 --> 00:31:43.200
Oh, no, that's not Doric.

500
00:31:45.320 --> 00:31:47.360
Move in! Kill her!

501
00:31:54.800 --> 00:31:55.800
Move in!

502
00:31:57.240 --> 00:31:58.360
Move in!

503
00:31:59.280 --> 00:32:00.280
That's her.

504
00:32:13.360 --> 00:32:15.360
- What is that again?
- It's an owlbear.

505
00:32:43.960 --> 00:32:45.320
<i>Mlor fol satu.</i>

506
00:32:46.360 --> 00:32:48.280
- <i>Silesna.</i>
- How high is this place?

507
00:32:48.360 --> 00:32:49.400
It's just up here.

508
00:32:50.240 --> 00:32:52.400
- Stay where you are!
- Wait! Wait! It's me!

509
00:32:53.240 --> 00:32:55.400
- Simon.
- Simon who?

510
00:32:55.480 --> 00:32:56.480
Ouch.

511
00:32:56.560 --> 00:32:58.520
Simon Aumar.

512
00:32:58.600 --> 00:32:59.640
Sorcerer.

513
00:33:00.160 --> 00:33:01.640
I courted you.

514
00:33:02.320 --> 00:33:03.960
You said I made you feel sad.

515
00:33:04.040 --> 00:33:06.920
Not from anything I did,
just from who I was.

516
00:33:09.760 --> 00:33:10.960
- Yeah.
- Yeah.

517
00:33:11.680 --> 00:33:12.680
What are you doing here?

518
00:33:12.960 --> 00:33:14.760
- We need a deer.
- We don't need a deer.

519
00:33:15.200 --> 00:33:17.000
We're gonna take down
Forge Fitzwilliam.

520
00:33:23.360 --> 00:33:24.640
So, how'd you come to live here?

521
00:33:24.840 --> 00:33:28.120
I was born to humans who decided
they didn't want a tiefling child.

522
00:33:28.920 --> 00:33:30.200
The wood elves took me in.

523
00:33:30.400 --> 00:33:32.240
I joined the Emerald Enclave
to protect them.

524
00:33:32.320 --> 00:33:34.000
See, that's all the more reason
to join us.

525
00:33:34.040 --> 00:33:36.520
You're the only one
who can get into that castle unseen

526
00:33:36.600 --> 00:33:38.120
and tell us what we're dealing with.

527
00:33:38.440 --> 00:33:40.640
As you can imagine,
I don't trust humans.

528
00:33:40.720 --> 00:33:42.560
I find you to be hateful and selfish.

529
00:33:42.960 --> 00:33:46.000
Well, I'm finding you
to be a little mean.

530
00:33:46.160 --> 00:33:48.000
If it helps, I'm only half-human.

531
00:33:48.160 --> 00:33:49.360
But you're a bad sorcerer.

532
00:33:49.440 --> 00:33:51.600
No, Simon... He's a mighty sorcerer!

533
00:33:51.920 --> 00:33:54.120
He's a descendant of Elminster Aumar.

534
00:33:54.360 --> 00:33:57.520
The only way to succeed in this is to
have confidence that it can be done.

535
00:33:58.120 --> 00:34:00.520
- He doesn't.
- Yeah, I suppose that's fair.

536
00:34:00.720 --> 00:34:04.480
Look, Simon may not have my wit
or Holga's strength

537
00:34:04.560 --> 00:34:06.560
but when it counts,
this young man delivers.

538
00:34:06.640 --> 00:34:07.640
It's why I chose him.

539
00:34:07.920 --> 00:34:09.680
He's also the only sorcerer you know.

540
00:34:09.760 --> 00:34:10.760
Holga, not helpful.

541
00:34:11.760 --> 00:34:13.600
What is it exactly
that you bring to this?

542
00:34:13.680 --> 00:34:16.400
Me? I'm a planner. You know?

543
00:34:16.880 --> 00:34:17.880
I make plans.

544
00:34:18.600 --> 00:34:21.160
You've already made the plan,
so what value do you have now?

545
00:34:22.280 --> 00:34:24.880
If the plan fails...
the existing plan...

546
00:34:24.960 --> 00:34:26.160
I make a new plan.

547
00:34:27.040 --> 00:34:28.200
So you make plans that fail.

548
00:34:28.280 --> 00:34:29.600
- No.
- He also plays the lute.

549
00:34:29.680 --> 00:34:32.200
Holga, not relevant.
Trust me, I'm indispensable.

550
00:34:35.880 --> 00:34:36.880
Well...

551
00:34:37.840 --> 00:34:40.840
none of the plans we've tried
to take down Forge have worked.

552
00:34:42.120 --> 00:34:44.480
We dared to question
how he came to power

553
00:34:44.800 --> 00:34:46.560
so he declared us enemies.

554
00:34:47.800 --> 00:34:49.560
Began destroying our homes

555
00:34:50.320 --> 00:34:52.200
and executing our people.

556
00:34:53.920 --> 00:34:55.920
If we don't stop Forge soon

557
00:34:56.680 --> 00:34:58.520
there'll be nothing left to defend.

558
00:35:01.920 --> 00:35:03.240
I'm not doing this for the money.

559
00:35:04.840 --> 00:35:07.520
I'm doing this for the people who
took me in when no one else would.

560
00:35:08.680 --> 00:35:10.240
So we'll keep your share then.

561
00:35:19.760 --> 00:35:20.760
Szass Tam.

562
00:35:21.640 --> 00:35:25.520
But you have always been
the disciple I rely on most.

563
00:35:27.280 --> 00:35:28.520
Doff your cowl.

564
00:35:29.480 --> 00:35:31.480
You needn't hide your sigils from me.

565
00:35:33.760 --> 00:35:35.760
I'd rather be flensed and flayed

566
00:35:35.840 --> 00:35:38.600
than spend another hour
with Forge Fitzwilliam.

567
00:35:39.240 --> 00:35:41.360
The man is insufferable.

568
00:35:43.800 --> 00:35:47.520
But we never would have come this far
without his "charm."

569
00:35:48.520 --> 00:35:51.640
The living have befouled
this world long enough.

570
00:35:53.520 --> 00:35:57.120
Take solace in knowing that
your work here is nearly complete.

571
00:36:00.080 --> 00:36:01.160
There you are!

572
00:36:02.480 --> 00:36:04.680
With your hood off, I notice.

573
00:36:06.200 --> 00:36:08.000
Probably best to keep that on.

574
00:36:08.320 --> 00:36:10.000
You know, you Red Wizards of Thay

575
00:36:10.320 --> 00:36:13.520
are not as popular
as you should be outside Thay.

576
00:36:13.680 --> 00:36:17.160
And of course, you're about
to be considerably less popular.

577
00:36:18.640 --> 00:36:22.480
But far, far be it from me
ever to tell you what to do.

578
00:36:23.440 --> 00:36:25.880
Caldwell and Piradost have arrived.
I was gonna give them...

579
00:36:27.680 --> 00:36:30.360
Awful, isn't it? I really have to do
something about these chairs.

580
00:36:30.680 --> 00:36:31.680
They're...

581
00:36:33.120 --> 00:36:36.720
Now, I think you will find that we
have taken every imaginable measure

582
00:36:36.800 --> 00:36:40.240
to protect the assets that
you may or may not choose to wager

583
00:36:40.320 --> 00:36:41.680
during the High Sun Games.

584
00:36:41.760 --> 00:36:44.960
We have new portcullises
on every wing of the castle.

585
00:36:45.200 --> 00:36:49.400
If the alarm is raised,
nobody gets in or out.

586
00:36:51.440 --> 00:36:53.880
And then there is...

587
00:36:54.240 --> 00:36:55.800
the vault itself.

588
00:36:57.600 --> 00:37:00.320
My chief adviser, Sofina,
can give you all the details.

589
00:37:03.200 --> 00:37:06.360
It is protected by
the Arcane Seal of Mordenkainen.

590
00:37:12.760 --> 00:37:13.800
Well...

591
00:37:14.200 --> 00:37:17.480
perhaps not all the details, but...

592
00:37:17.800 --> 00:37:20.960
suffice to say
it is a seriously powerful spell.

593
00:37:21.040 --> 00:37:23.600
Might I inquire, what prompted you
to resume the games?

594
00:37:23.680 --> 00:37:25.960
Lord Neverember considered them
quite brutal.

595
00:37:26.040 --> 00:37:28.000
Lord Neverember and I
are very different men.

596
00:37:28.080 --> 00:37:29.800
For example, I prefer
to be up and about.

597
00:37:29.880 --> 00:37:31.800
He prefers to be
in a vegetative state.

598
00:37:33.680 --> 00:37:35.120
You are terrible.

599
00:37:36.080 --> 00:37:37.480
I can be naughty.

600
00:37:37.720 --> 00:37:41.080
The truth is that the games bring
the city together like nothing else.

601
00:37:41.160 --> 00:37:46.200
And it is not the role of government
to deny the people what they crave.

602
00:37:46.880 --> 00:37:50.720
Or to deny you rich bastards
the right to profit off them.

603
00:37:52.920 --> 00:37:55.000
Now who wants refreshments?

604
00:37:55.080 --> 00:37:56.120
Silence!

605
00:37:59.160 --> 00:38:01.560
A Wild Shape is among us.

606
00:38:29.160 --> 00:38:30.160
Hey!

607
00:38:30.560 --> 00:38:31.560
Stop!

608
00:38:38.720 --> 00:38:39.800
I can't grab her!

609
00:40:29.760 --> 00:40:32.120
So she did become a deer.

610
00:40:32.200 --> 00:40:33.400
Only at the very end.

611
00:40:33.800 --> 00:40:35.600
Are you absolutely sure about Sofina?

612
00:40:35.680 --> 00:40:36.720
I saw her markings.

613
00:40:36.800 --> 00:40:38.560
No wonder I couldn't
counter her Time Stop.

614
00:40:38.640 --> 00:40:39.680
Forge knew all along.

615
00:40:39.760 --> 00:40:41.576
He's got my daughter in there
with a Red Wizard.

616
00:40:41.600 --> 00:40:45.920
The vault is protected by something
called "Morty Kamen's Arcane Seal."

617
00:40:46.120 --> 00:40:48.240
- Mordenkainen?
- Yeah, that's it.

618
00:40:48.320 --> 00:40:50.280
- Oh, pity.
- What?

619
00:40:50.480 --> 00:40:52.696
If the vault has Mordenkainen's Seal,
we're not getting in.

620
00:40:52.720 --> 00:40:54.960
- It's impenetrable.
- Can't you just open it with magic?

621
00:40:55.440 --> 00:40:56.640
Okay, here we go.

622
00:40:56.720 --> 00:41:00.120
I hate how everyone thinks that
you can solve any problem with magic.

623
00:41:00.200 --> 00:41:03.120
There are limits.
This isn't some bedtime story.

624
00:41:03.200 --> 00:41:04.520
This is the real world.

625
00:41:04.800 --> 00:41:06.000
So there's no way to open it?

626
00:41:06.320 --> 00:41:10.000
I mean, if I were one of the world's
most powerful sorcerers, so, no.

627
00:41:10.080 --> 00:41:11.760
Or if we had the Helm of Disjunction.

628
00:41:12.560 --> 00:41:13.560
The what?

629
00:41:13.640 --> 00:41:15.760
It's a helmet that disables
all nearby enchantments.

630
00:41:15.840 --> 00:41:16.880
But it doesn't matter.

631
00:41:16.960 --> 00:41:18.680
The thing went missing ages ago.
We're done.

632
00:41:19.360 --> 00:41:20.360
Come on.

633
00:41:20.960 --> 00:41:23.760
What's the problem?
We can find that helmet.

634
00:41:23.840 --> 00:41:26.120
Even if we did, I couldn't use it
without attuning to it

635
00:41:26.200 --> 00:41:27.200
which I'm terrible at.

636
00:41:27.280 --> 00:41:28.600
You can do it. I know you can.

637
00:41:28.680 --> 00:41:30.200
You saying that doesn't make it so.

638
00:41:30.280 --> 00:41:31.600
Yeah, but you saying it does.

639
00:41:31.680 --> 00:41:32.960
- But I can't.
- But you can.

640
00:41:33.040 --> 00:41:34.320
- But I won't.
- Just say it.

641
00:41:34.400 --> 00:41:35.400
- No!
- Fine.

642
00:41:35.480 --> 00:41:36.736
Can we just keep this between us?

643
00:41:36.760 --> 00:41:38.320
I don't want to hurt
the group's morale.

644
00:41:38.400 --> 00:41:39.840
What morale?

645
00:41:41.440 --> 00:41:42.880
Holga knows where the helmet is.

646
00:41:42.960 --> 00:41:44.280
- You do?
- My tribe

647
00:41:44.360 --> 00:41:46.760
fought the Cult of the Dragon
over it at the Evermoors.

648
00:41:46.840 --> 00:41:48.176
We could just ask them where it went.

649
00:41:48.200 --> 00:41:50.840
That battle was a century ago.
They're all dead.

650
00:41:50.920 --> 00:41:52.440
So? Ask them with magic.

651
00:41:52.520 --> 00:41:55.320
He just made a whole speech how
he can't fix everything with magic.

652
00:41:55.400 --> 00:41:56.920
Actually, that is something I can do.

653
00:41:58.200 --> 00:41:59.520
You can bring back the dead?

654
00:41:59.960 --> 00:42:01.520
I can't bring them back

655
00:42:01.600 --> 00:42:04.400
but I have this token that lets me
ask corpses some questions

656
00:42:04.480 --> 00:42:05.920
then they go back to being dead.

657
00:42:06.280 --> 00:42:08.080
- Yuck.
- Yeah, it's fairly horrible.

658
00:42:08.160 --> 00:42:10.000
It's fairly wonderful.

659
00:42:10.480 --> 00:42:13.360
We're off to the Evermoors.
Thank you, Simon, for the drinks.

660
00:42:14.160 --> 00:42:15.280
What? No...

661
00:42:15.360 --> 00:42:16.880
Just pay it with magic.

662
00:42:56.320 --> 00:42:57.360
He's a Thayan!

663
00:43:21.440 --> 00:43:22.440
Hey, Ed.

664
00:43:24.200 --> 00:43:25.200
Look where we are.

665
00:43:26.240 --> 00:43:27.720
Marlamin? Really?

666
00:43:27.880 --> 00:43:29.360
Why would you do that to yourself?

667
00:43:29.800 --> 00:43:31.680
I'm just gonna pick up
some of my things.

668
00:43:36.920 --> 00:43:38.600
He painted the shutters.

669
00:43:39.480 --> 00:43:40.480
Pretty.

670
00:43:48.680 --> 00:43:49.720
Holga!

671
00:43:50.080 --> 00:43:51.160
Hello, Marlamin.

672
00:43:51.800 --> 00:43:53.520
- That's Marlamin?
- Yeah.

673
00:43:54.280 --> 00:43:56.560
We were all a little surprised
the first time we met him.

674
00:43:57.600 --> 00:43:59.520
I thought your sentence was longer.

675
00:44:00.120 --> 00:44:01.520
I busted out of there.

676
00:44:04.320 --> 00:44:05.800
Same old Holga.

677
00:44:08.240 --> 00:44:09.680
So what have you been up to?

678
00:44:11.960 --> 00:44:13.000
The usual.

679
00:44:13.320 --> 00:44:15.680
I've got my garden.
I'm working on my book.

680
00:44:16.000 --> 00:44:18.480
I see you still have
that walking stick I gave you.

681
00:44:18.720 --> 00:44:20.960
Yeah. Yeah.

682
00:44:21.040 --> 00:44:23.040
Well, you can take it with you
if you want.

683
00:44:23.160 --> 00:44:25.080
- Gwinn's not much for rambling.
- Gwinn?

684
00:44:25.160 --> 00:44:26.720
- You home, darling?
- In here.

685
00:44:28.080 --> 00:44:29.920
Squashed a pack of bullywugs
down at the...

686
00:44:30.320 --> 00:44:31.360
Hello.

687
00:44:31.640 --> 00:44:34.080
- Who's this, then?
- Gwinn, this is Holga.

688
00:44:35.960 --> 00:44:37.040
Heard a lot about you.

689
00:44:37.880 --> 00:44:39.200
I'd shake your hand, but...

690
00:44:39.720 --> 00:44:40.720
Pleasure.

691
00:44:40.800 --> 00:44:42.040
How long you in town for?

692
00:44:42.840 --> 00:44:44.000
Just passing through.

693
00:44:44.080 --> 00:44:46.480
Gonna talk to some corpses
south of Nesmé.

694
00:44:46.560 --> 00:44:47.680
Great, yeah.

695
00:44:49.520 --> 00:44:50.840
Gonna get washed up for supper.

696
00:44:51.080 --> 00:44:52.080
What we having?

697
00:44:52.160 --> 00:44:54.240
I cured a goose
and I gathered some pickleberries.

698
00:44:55.560 --> 00:44:56.560
Nice meeting you, Holga.

699
00:45:01.280 --> 00:45:02.480
So how long have you two...

700
00:45:02.560 --> 00:45:03.560
Going on a year.

701
00:45:04.680 --> 00:45:06.040
Does she make you happy?

702
00:45:06.640 --> 00:45:07.960
Happier than I did?

703
00:45:09.720 --> 00:45:12.080
I'll put it this way:
She makes her living honestly.

704
00:45:12.160 --> 00:45:14.360
She doesn't drink herself silly.

705
00:45:16.320 --> 00:45:19.320
And she doesn't make me weep
in the small hours

706
00:45:19.400 --> 00:45:20.680
wondering where she is.

707
00:45:21.360 --> 00:45:22.720
I was in pain.

708
00:45:22.800 --> 00:45:25.440
I was banished from my damn tribe
to be with you.

709
00:45:25.520 --> 00:45:28.160
And I tried to build us a home
so you could forget that.

710
00:45:30.880 --> 00:45:32.040
But you never could.

711
00:45:35.120 --> 00:45:36.520
Gwinn seems lovely.

712
00:45:37.960 --> 00:45:39.040
You deserve that.

713
00:45:39.600 --> 00:45:40.640
Thank you.

714
00:45:41.720 --> 00:45:43.800
You know, when you left,
I lost my family.

715
00:45:46.080 --> 00:45:48.320
I've been fortunate enough
to find another.

716
00:45:50.240 --> 00:45:52.720
And I wish nothing
less than that for you.

717
00:45:56.760 --> 00:45:58.160
My sweet, old Ho-Ho.

718
00:46:12.400 --> 00:46:13.920
We're gonna take down Forge.

719
00:46:14.840 --> 00:46:17.280
I'm gonna show
Marlamin and the Elk tribe

720
00:46:17.360 --> 00:46:18.880
they were fools to let me go.

721
00:46:35.840 --> 00:46:40.120
<i>Not fortune found, nor fate divine</i>

722
00:46:40.520 --> 00:46:44.320
<i>Come close to toping
the juice of the vine</i>

723
00:46:45.040 --> 00:46:48.600
<i>With cherry crew, we sip and sway</i>

724
00:46:48.680 --> 00:46:52.040
<i>Let's tip the tankard
and waste the day</i>

725
00:46:52.640 --> 00:46:55.480
<i>- Ree-raw! Well, ye ken
- Ree-raw! Well, ye ken</i>

726
00:46:55.560 --> 00:46:58.120
<i>- Our toils can wait for a time
- Our toils can wait for a time</i>

727
00:46:58.760 --> 00:47:01.600
<i>- We saw the folly of men
- We saw the folly of men</i>

728
00:47:01.680 --> 00:47:04.360
<i>- Who rather than revel repine
- Who rather than revel repine</i>

729
00:47:04.640 --> 00:47:07.160
<i>- Ree-raw! Well, ye ken
