<i>- Our toils can wait for a time
- Our toils can wait for a time</i>

731
00:47:10.400 --> 00:47:12.960
<i>- We saw the folly of men
- We saw the folly of men</i>

732
00:47:13.040 --> 00:47:15.880
<i>- Who rather than revel repine
- Who rather than revel repine</i>

733
00:47:35.600 --> 00:47:38.760
So many of my kin
gave their lives in battle here.

734
00:47:40.600 --> 00:47:43.920
I'd always imagined I'd be buried
in sacred ground like this.

735
00:47:44.440 --> 00:47:45.440
Yeah.

736
00:47:46.040 --> 00:47:47.200
Anyone got a shovel?

737
00:47:53.800 --> 00:47:55.760
Okay, Simon, how does this work?

738
00:47:56.320 --> 00:47:59.040
I read the incantation
on this cleric's token.

739
00:47:59.120 --> 00:48:01.040
Should be here somewhere. Here!

740
00:48:02.080 --> 00:48:04.280
All right.
Once the dead man is revived

741
00:48:04.360 --> 00:48:05.880
we can ask him five questions

742
00:48:05.960 --> 00:48:08.800
at which point he will die again,
never to be re-revived.

743
00:48:08.880 --> 00:48:10.040
Why five questions?

744
00:48:10.120 --> 00:48:11.640
I don't know,
that's just how it works.

745
00:48:11.680 --> 00:48:13.880
- Seems arbitrary.
- Can we get on with this, please?

746
00:48:13.960 --> 00:48:15.040
Right, yes.

747
00:48:23.160 --> 00:48:24.200
Delightful.

748
00:48:30.800 --> 00:48:32.560
<i>Perlamon tergatys.</i>

749
00:48:36.400 --> 00:48:37.600
Maybe I'm not saying it right.

750
00:48:41.920 --> 00:48:43.400
I wasn't scared, merely startled.

751
00:48:45.320 --> 00:48:46.360
Here we go.

752
00:48:47.800 --> 00:48:49.640
Were you killed
in the Battle of the Evermoors?

753
00:48:49.800 --> 00:48:51.360
- Yes.
- Great!

754
00:48:51.720 --> 00:48:55.600
I mean, not for you.
Sorry for your loss.

755
00:48:56.200 --> 00:48:58.120
- Four more questions, right?
- Yes.

756
00:48:58.560 --> 00:49:00.200
No, no, that wasn't for you.

757
00:49:00.360 --> 00:49:01.560
Did that count as a question?

758
00:49:01.640 --> 00:49:02.640
Yes.

759
00:49:02.720 --> 00:49:03.720
Damn it.

760
00:49:04.240 --> 00:49:06.320
Only answer when I talk to you

761
00:49:06.400 --> 00:49:07.600
- okay?
- Yes.

762
00:49:07.680 --> 00:49:09.520
Why did you say "okay?"
at the end of that?

763
00:49:09.600 --> 00:49:10.640
I didn't.

764
00:49:12.120 --> 00:49:13.600
Fantastic. Where's the shovel?

765
00:49:15.480 --> 00:49:16.920
<i>Perlamon tergatys.</i>

766
00:49:21.160 --> 00:49:22.160
Toke Horgath.

767
00:49:23.640 --> 00:49:26.880
During the battle, did you see
the Helmet of Disjunction?

768
00:49:27.160 --> 00:49:31.320
It was in possession of my chief,
Stanhard Grimwulf.

769
00:49:31.560 --> 00:49:32.560
Okay, good.

770
00:49:33.000 --> 00:49:34.880
And what did
Stanhard Grimwulf do with it?

771
00:49:36.840 --> 00:49:41.320
<i>As the cultists breached the ridge,
we knew we outnumbered them.</i>

772
00:49:41.400 --> 00:49:45.680
<i>But our advantage meant nothing
against the dragon Rakor.</i>

773
00:49:54.800 --> 00:49:55.880
Horgath!

774
00:49:56.640 --> 00:49:57.640
Horgath!

775
00:49:58.960 --> 00:50:00.680
Take this and run.

776
00:50:01.000 --> 00:50:03.360
Keep it from Rakor at all costs!

777
00:50:03.640 --> 00:50:05.280
Understood, sir. Don't worry.

778
00:50:05.520 --> 00:50:07.560
That's the last thing I remember.

779
00:50:11.960 --> 00:50:13.000
Yeah, well...

780
00:50:14.560 --> 00:50:15.680
Thanks for your help.

781
00:50:16.200 --> 00:50:18.040
Let's go look
for Stanhard Grimwulf's grave.

782
00:50:18.120 --> 00:50:19.280
Hang on! Hang on!

783
00:50:19.560 --> 00:50:21.640
Aren't you going to ask him
the last three questions?

784
00:50:21.680 --> 00:50:23.576
Ask him what? He already
told us everything he knows.

785
00:50:23.600 --> 00:50:26.160
Well, you can't just leave him
like that. Look at the poor bloke.

786
00:50:27.640 --> 00:50:28.640
Fine.

787
00:50:30.360 --> 00:50:31.400
What's your favorite food?

788
00:50:32.160 --> 00:50:34.120
Oats. No, barley!

789
00:50:34.440 --> 00:50:35.440
Oh, boy.

790
00:50:36.720 --> 00:50:37.800
Do you like cats?

791
00:50:38.160 --> 00:50:39.160
Not really.

792
00:50:39.440 --> 00:50:40.440
Okay.

793
00:50:40.840 --> 00:50:41.920
What's two plus two?

794
00:50:42.000 --> 00:50:43.120
I'm bad at math.

795
00:50:44.120 --> 00:50:45.360
- Don't you feel better?
- No.

796
00:50:48.000 --> 00:50:51.640
Oftentimes, the most onerous decision
a leader can take

797
00:50:51.720 --> 00:50:53.200
is when to retreat.

798
00:50:54.360 --> 00:50:55.800
I issued the order.

799
00:50:58.120 --> 00:51:00.880
<i>I commanded my battle lord
to deliver the helmet</i>

800
00:51:00.960 --> 00:51:03.200
<i>to our swiftest rider, Ven Salafin.</i>

801
00:51:03.280 --> 00:51:05.360
If we can just make it
over the ridge, we can...

802
00:51:07.000 --> 00:51:08.000
Not again.

803
00:51:10.080 --> 00:51:11.800
It was the morning of the battle.

804
00:51:13.400 --> 00:51:16.680
As I stepped out my bath,
my foot slipped on the stone.

805
00:51:21.000 --> 00:51:22.520
And then you went into the battle?

806
00:51:22.600 --> 00:51:25.880
No. I died. From the fall.

807
00:51:25.960 --> 00:51:28.840
But Stanhard Grimwulf said
he gave the helmet to Ven Salafin.

808
00:51:28.920 --> 00:51:29.920
That's you, isn't it?

809
00:51:30.880 --> 00:51:34.120
I'm Sven Salafin. Ven's my brother.

810
00:51:34.560 --> 00:51:35.920
This is a nightmare.

811
00:51:36.520 --> 00:51:37.600
Is Ven all right?

812
00:51:40.400 --> 00:51:44.360
I was wounded and had lost my horse
as I escaped the field of battle.

813
00:51:44.880 --> 00:51:46.520
<i>I didn't care about myself.</i>

814
00:51:46.800 --> 00:51:48.920
<i>I just needed
to keep the helmet safe.</i>

815
00:51:58.280 --> 00:52:01.680
<i>It was a Thayan,
who bore the mark of Szass Tam.</i>

816
00:52:04.800 --> 00:52:06.560
<i>I waited for the killing blow.</i>

817
00:52:07.360 --> 00:52:08.640
<i>But it never came.</i>

818
00:52:09.760 --> 00:52:11.240
<i>He had a kind way.</i>

819
00:52:11.760 --> 00:52:14.280
<i>He told me his name was Xenk Yendar.</i>

820
00:52:14.360 --> 00:52:17.160
<i>He had fled Szass Tam
and now lived in exile.</i>

821
00:52:17.520 --> 00:52:20.760
<i>As I died, he promised
to keep the helmet safe.</i>

822
00:52:21.400 --> 00:52:23.320
And for some reason, I believed him.

823
00:52:23.400 --> 00:52:25.640
You're joking. A "kind" Thayan?

824
00:52:25.720 --> 00:52:26.760
I speak truth.

825
00:52:26.840 --> 00:52:28.000
You speak horseshit.

826
00:52:28.320 --> 00:52:30.160
That Thayan lied
and you died for nothing.

827
00:52:31.080 --> 00:52:33.336
The helmet's a dead end, we'll have
to find another way into the vault.

828
00:52:33.360 --> 00:52:34.680
No, I've heard of Xenk.

829
00:52:35.160 --> 00:52:37.760
He's a paladin. He helped the Enclave
defeat the Clerics of Talos.

830
00:52:37.800 --> 00:52:40.400
I know the name as well. My uncle
said Xenk fended off a Beholder

831
00:52:40.480 --> 00:52:42.160
using only a sharpened gourd.

832
00:52:42.680 --> 00:52:43.720
A sharpened gourd?

833
00:52:43.920 --> 00:52:44.920
Something sharp.

834
00:52:45.000 --> 00:52:47.960
The Thayans are murderers.
End of story.

835
00:52:49.960 --> 00:52:50.960
What?

836
00:52:51.040 --> 00:52:52.520
- I've heard of him, too.
- No.

837
00:52:52.600 --> 00:52:54.520
He fought with my cousin
in the Anauroch.

838
00:52:54.600 --> 00:52:55.640
He says he's a good man.

839
00:52:55.720 --> 00:52:59.440
Well, you can all go find this lovely
Xenk and braid each other's hair.

840
00:52:59.520 --> 00:53:00.800
I'll find another way.

841
00:53:03.120 --> 00:53:04.120
What's his problem?

842
00:53:04.200 --> 00:53:05.880
He's got a history with the Thayans.

843
00:53:06.560 --> 00:53:10.000
I know how you're feeling.
But we're running out of time.

844
00:53:12.600 --> 00:53:14.120
I'd be betraying Zia.

845
00:53:14.560 --> 00:53:17.880
No, you wouldn't. You'd be
doing it to save her and Kira.

846
00:53:18.440 --> 00:53:20.600
Look, if Xenk turns out to be a prick

847
00:53:20.800 --> 00:53:22.360
I'll split him
right down the middle.

848
00:53:23.200 --> 00:53:24.240
That's very sweet.

849
00:53:24.320 --> 00:53:25.640
What have we got to lose?

850
00:53:29.640 --> 00:53:31.080
Anyone know where stupid Xenk is?

851
00:53:31.680 --> 00:53:34.320
Last I heard, he was working with
the Harpers in Mornbryn's Shield.

852
00:53:34.440 --> 00:53:36.200
Great! Harpers.

853
00:53:36.480 --> 00:53:37.760
What's his problem with Harpers?

854
00:53:37.840 --> 00:53:39.480
He's got a history with them too.

855
00:53:39.560 --> 00:53:40.680
All right, let's go.

856
00:53:41.800 --> 00:53:42.920
Excuse me?

857
00:53:44.120 --> 00:53:45.640
I'm still alive.

858
00:53:45.720 --> 00:53:46.720
Right.

859
00:53:48.600 --> 00:53:49.880
What's your favorite book?

860
00:53:50.640 --> 00:53:52.000
Hard to pick just one.

861
00:53:53.280 --> 00:53:54.456
- Fifth question, right?
- Yep.

862
00:53:54.480 --> 00:53:57.360
In terms of historical works, I'd say

863
00:53:57.440 --> 00:54:00.240
<i>The Fanged Tome of Lykanthus Szar.</i>

864
00:54:01.480 --> 00:54:03.400
That was only the fourth question.

865
00:54:04.320 --> 00:54:05.360
Hello?

866
00:54:06.560 --> 00:54:07.760
Oh, shit.

867
00:54:10.800 --> 00:54:12.520
Heave! Heave!

868
00:54:12.600 --> 00:54:14.160
Come on, we need more! Come on!

869
00:54:46.680 --> 00:54:48.240
It's alive!

870
00:54:50.600 --> 00:54:51.600
Thank you!

871
00:55:03.760 --> 00:55:04.760
He's interesting.

872
00:55:05.000 --> 00:55:06.160
I've seen more interesting.

873
00:55:06.240 --> 00:55:07.240
Ed, go talk to him.

874
00:55:07.320 --> 00:55:08.320
You go talk to him.

875
00:55:08.400 --> 00:55:09.960
You know,
I've pulled cats out of fish.

876
00:55:18.240 --> 00:55:19.320
Xenk, is it?

877
00:55:21.120 --> 00:55:22.536
That is a query
I prefer not to answer

878
00:55:22.560 --> 00:55:24.120
without knowing
to whom I am speaking.

879
00:55:24.200 --> 00:55:25.720
I'm Holga Kilgore.

880
00:55:26.040 --> 00:55:28.680
This is Simon, Edgin
and Doric back there.

881
00:55:30.000 --> 00:55:31.576
And what brings you
to Mornbryn's Shield?

882
00:55:31.600 --> 00:55:32.600
You do.

883
00:55:33.200 --> 00:55:35.240
We're trying to find
the Helmet of Dysfunction.

884
00:55:35.320 --> 00:55:36.360
Disjunction.

885
00:55:37.000 --> 00:55:38.840
Many lives were lost
in defense of that helm.

886
00:55:38.920 --> 00:55:41.280
To speak of it would be
to diminish their sacrifice.

887
00:55:45.040 --> 00:55:46.120
<i>Janklee.</i>

888
00:55:47.160 --> 00:55:49.560
<i>Janklee</i> to you as well, good sir.

889
00:55:53.680 --> 00:55:56.440
You're known as a man
of honor and integrity

890
00:55:56.520 --> 00:55:57.760
and I can assure you

891
00:55:57.840 --> 00:56:00.600
our reasons for wanting the helmet
are entirely noble.

892
00:56:00.680 --> 00:56:02.160
Yep. We're gonna rob someone.

893
00:56:02.240 --> 00:56:03.240
Holga!

894
00:56:03.760 --> 00:56:06.160
Not just anyone. Forge Fitzwilliam.

895
00:56:06.480 --> 00:56:08.320
And the Red Wizard of Thay
he's partnered with.

896
00:56:10.360 --> 00:56:11.360
Come with me.

897
00:56:16.120 --> 00:56:17.520
What is this place?

898
00:56:17.600 --> 00:56:19.320
A Harper sanctuary.

899
00:56:20.200 --> 00:56:22.280
But surely your friend Edgin
already knew that.

900
00:56:24.000 --> 00:56:25.280
How'd you know I was a Harper?

901
00:56:25.360 --> 00:56:27.440
You may have forsworn your oath

902
00:56:28.400 --> 00:56:30.560
but your oath hasn't forsworn you.

903
00:56:31.800 --> 00:56:33.376
Just because
that sentence is symmetrical

904
00:56:33.400 --> 00:56:34.800
doesn't make it not nonsense.

905
00:56:35.120 --> 00:56:36.520
Why do you wish to rob Fitzwilliam?

906
00:56:36.600 --> 00:56:39.400
He stole Edgin's daughter
and a great deal of treasure from us.

907
00:56:39.480 --> 00:56:40.800
Also a Tablet of Reawakening.

908
00:56:40.880 --> 00:56:42.200
He doesn't need to know all that.

909
00:56:42.880 --> 00:56:44.320
- I was just...
- In other words

910
00:56:44.400 --> 00:56:46.000
Forge is a real son of a bitch.

911
00:56:46.240 --> 00:56:48.080
So you blame his mother
for his corruption.

912
00:56:48.320 --> 00:56:49.320
What?

913
00:56:49.560 --> 00:56:51.120
No, it's an expression.

914
00:56:51.360 --> 00:56:52.480
I see.

915
00:56:52.840 --> 00:56:54.800
I do not traffic in colloquialisms.

916
00:56:55.800 --> 00:56:57.480
You're not a lot of fun, are you?

917
00:56:58.000 --> 00:56:59.880
If Fitzwilliam is truly allied
with a Red Wizard

918
00:56:59.920 --> 00:57:02.640
their intentions must go
beyond the mere political.

919
00:57:03.440 --> 00:57:05.720
Over a century ago,
the necromancer Szass Tam

920
00:57:05.800 --> 00:57:08.440
was one of eight zulkirs
who ruled the nation of Thay.

921
00:57:08.520 --> 00:57:09.920
Great, a history lesson.

922
00:57:10.080 --> 00:57:11.960
But Tam's hunger for power
was absolute.

923
00:57:13.440 --> 00:57:15.120
On the eve of the solstice

924
00:57:15.200 --> 00:57:18.120
<i>the residents of the capital
gathered for a celebration.</i>

925
00:57:23.440 --> 00:57:26.760
<i>Unbeknownst to them,
or his fellow rulers</i>

926
00:57:27.080 --> 00:57:28.920
<i>Tam had a plan of his own:</i>

927
00:57:29.680 --> 00:57:31.960
<i>to stage an unholy coup.</i>

928
00:57:57.280 --> 00:57:59.520
<i>He unleashed the Beckoning Death</i>

929
00:57:59.600 --> 00:58:03.120
<i>a spell that would consume
the souls of all who beheld it</i>

930
00:58:03.200 --> 00:58:05.160
<i>enslaving them to his will.</i>

931
00:58:05.920 --> 00:58:07.840
<i>With the aid of his Red Wizards</i>

932
00:58:07.920 --> 00:58:10.840
<i>Szass Tam created
an army of the undead</i>

933
00:58:11.160 --> 00:58:14.000
<i>allowing him to conquer
the entire nation.</i>

934
00:58:17.360 --> 00:58:20.000
Szass's power extends no further
than the borders of Thay.

935
00:58:20.400 --> 00:58:22.440
I suspect he and his Red Wizards
will not be content

936
00:58:22.480 --> 00:58:25.280
until they have infected the whole
of Faerûn with their maleficence.

937
00:58:25.360 --> 00:58:28.120
You done? Because we already know
that Red Wizards are bad.

938
00:58:28.200 --> 00:58:30.200
And so does Forge.
The question remains

939
00:58:30.280 --> 00:58:32.760
if they helped him to take power,
what do they stand to gain?

940
00:58:32.840 --> 00:58:34.520
Sounds like we have a common enemy.

941
00:58:34.600 --> 00:58:36.600
You give us that helmet,
and we take Forge down.

942
00:58:36.800 --> 00:58:38.776
No one stays Lord without a fortune
to back him up.

943
00:58:38.800 --> 00:58:40.520
And the Red Wizards
lose their puppet.

944
00:58:41.000 --> 00:58:42.720
What will become of
the wealth you burgle?

945
00:58:43.240 --> 00:58:44.240
What does that matter?

946
00:58:44.320 --> 00:58:47.120
I will not be complicit in
the illicit use of ill-gotten booty.

947
00:58:48.880 --> 00:58:51.400
Fine. We'll divide it
amongst the townspeople.

948
00:58:51.480 --> 00:58:53.200
- Swear to it.
- What?

949
00:58:53.640 --> 00:58:55.320
Place your hand on this Harper's Seal

950
00:58:55.520 --> 00:58:58.680
and swear that you will indeed
distribute all the wealth you take

951
00:58:58.760 --> 00:59:00.560
amongst the people of Neverwinter.

952
00:59:00.800 --> 00:59:01.880
Sure, fine.

953
00:59:06.560 --> 00:59:07.680
Go on, Ed.

954
00:59:08.440 --> 00:59:10.560
Promise you'll give Forge's money
to the people.

955
00:59:15.960 --> 00:59:17.080
I promise I'll...

956
00:59:17.720 --> 00:59:20.000
give Forge's money
to the people of Neverwinter.

957
00:59:20.680 --> 00:59:21.760
Keep this.

958
00:59:23.160 --> 00:59:26.240
You may not yet believe
your words, but I do.

959
00:59:27.840 --> 00:59:30.400
Yeah. Good for you.
Simon, hold onto this.

960
00:59:30.920 --> 00:59:32.320
Now, where's the helmet?

961
00:59:32.400 --> 00:59:33.720
In the bowels of the Underdark.

962
00:59:33.800 --> 00:59:34.800
The Underdark?

963
00:59:34.880 --> 00:59:36.736
Weren't you trying to keep it safe?
Why would you put it down there?

964
00:59:36.760 --> 00:59:37.816
Because it is the last place

965
00:59:37.840 --> 00:59:39.456
that anyone who
values their life would go.

966
00:59:39.480 --> 00:59:41.120
- Sounds lovely.
- Quite the opposite.

967
00:59:42.320 --> 00:59:43.920
I know. I was being ironic.

968
00:59:44.200 --> 00:59:47.400
I find irony is a blade that cuts
he who wields it most especially.

969
00:59:47.680 --> 00:59:50.320
Yeah? Is that what you find, Xenk?

970
00:59:51.360 --> 00:59:52.976
There is an entrance east
of the Sword Mountains

971
00:59:53.000 --> 00:59:54.240
in the Kryptgarden Forest

972
00:59:54.520 --> 00:59:56.760
from which we may descend
to the ruins of Dolblunde.

973
00:59:58.520 --> 01:00:01.960
If I may be so bold, what caused you
to renounce the Harpers?

974
01:00:04.720 --> 01:00:06.800
Being a Harper got my wife killed.

975
01:00:07.240 --> 01:00:08.280
I'm sorry.

976
01:00:09.320 --> 01:00:10.960
Did her assailants find justice?

977
01:00:11.240 --> 01:00:12.680
The Thayans, you mean?

978
01:00:14.160 --> 01:00:15.200
No.

979
01:00:15.280 --> 01:00:17.120
The Thayans are not all malevolent.

980
01:00:18.360 --> 01:00:21.080
I was a boy when Szass Tam
seized control of Thay.

981
01:00:23.840 --> 01:00:26.200
<i>I saw firsthand
the horrors of the spell.</i>

982
01:00:27.440 --> 01:00:29.640
<i>Honorable men turned to monsters.</i>

983
01:00:30.160 --> 01:00:32.480
<i>Minds wiped clean in moments.</i>

984
01:00:33.400 --> 01:00:36.640
<i>Parents turning on their own child.</i>

985
01:00:56.040 --> 01:00:58.480
<i>I escaped, alive</i>

986
01:00:59.560 --> 01:01:00.880
but forever changed.

987
01:01:02.200 --> 01:01:04.560
You and I have both lost
a part of ourselves.

988
01:01:05.480 --> 01:01:07.880
All that matters is
what we do with what remains.

989
01:01:09.000 --> 01:01:10.096
I told you what I'm gonna do.

990
01:01:10.120 --> 01:01:12.520
I'm gonna break into Castle Never
and get my family back.

991
01:01:13.200 --> 01:01:14.240
And the tablet?

992
01:01:14.560 --> 01:01:16.560
- You plan to resurrect your wife.
- Yeah.

993
01:01:17.680 --> 01:01:18.680
Very well.

994
01:01:19.360 --> 01:01:20.640
I'd only ask that you consider

995
01:01:20.720 --> 01:01:22.800
that this plane we call "life"
is but one of many.

996
01:01:23.720 --> 01:01:26.080
To drag your lady-love
back to her old life

997
01:01:26.360 --> 01:01:27.800
is to deprive her of her new one.

998
01:01:27.880 --> 01:01:30.160
Can someone else
ride next to this guy?

999
01:01:39.840 --> 01:01:41.400
Follow me to the orifice.

1000
01:01:44.520 --> 01:01:45.720
The orifice?

1001
01:01:47.560 --> 01:01:49.760
The Underdark has many entrances.

1002
01:01:52.720 --> 01:01:54.680
This is one of the less conspicuous.

1003
01:02:02.280 --> 01:02:03.400
I'll go last.

1004
01:02:05.360 --> 01:02:06.560
It's a day's trek.

1005
01:02:06.880 --> 01:02:08.640
I've chosen a path
to avoid the populace.

1006
01:02:08.720 --> 01:02:10.560
Stay close and quiet.

1007
01:02:11.120 --> 01:02:12.680
Whatever you've heard of this place

1008
01:02:12.760 --> 01:02:15.040
is merely a fraction
of its true danger.

1009
01:02:16.520 --> 01:02:18.200
Should the way become too dim

1010
01:02:18.560 --> 01:02:21.360
you may take my hand,
and I will lead you.

1011
01:02:24.360 --> 01:02:26.680
I'll tell you right now,
I'm not taking his hand.

1012
01:02:38.120 --> 01:02:40.360
Keep your guard up.
I don't trust this guy.

1013
01:02:41.440 --> 01:02:42.920
Even though he's helping us?

1014
01:02:43.920 --> 01:02:46.000
He's got something up his sleeve.

1015
01:02:46.080 --> 01:02:48.200
The only thing up my sleeve
is my arm.

1016
01:02:48.600 --> 01:02:49.600
How could he hear that?

1017
01:02:49.840 --> 01:02:51.000
I hear that as well.

1018
01:02:51.880 --> 01:02:52.880
I hate you.

1019
01:03:06.360 --> 01:03:08.320
The path to the ruins is just here.

1020
01:03:16.640 --> 01:03:17.640
Keep still!

1021
01:03:20.960 --> 01:03:22.000
Rochnon.

1022
01:03:22.280 --> 01:03:24.800
Intellect devourers.
Small but formidable.

1023
01:03:25.200 --> 01:03:27.240
They stun their targets
and consume the brain

1024
01:03:27.320 --> 01:03:28.840
taking control of the body.

1025
01:03:28.960 --> 01:03:30.640
- What do we do?
- Make no sound.

1026
01:03:31.880 --> 01:03:33.560
They're drawn to mental energy.

1027
01:03:34.120 --> 01:03:36.200
The higher
the intelligence of the prey

1028
01:03:36.480 --> 01:03:38.400
the more likely they are to strike.

1029
01:03:54.680 --> 01:03:56.120
Well, that's a little hurtful.

1030
01:03:57.600 --> 01:04:00.880
There it is.
The Hanging City of Dolblunde.

1031
01:04:02.320 --> 01:04:05.000
The helmet lies
on the far side of this chasm.

1032
01:04:06.120 --> 01:04:10.200
But be warned, the bridge is
protected by an ancient Gnomish trap.

1033
01:04:10.520 --> 01:04:12.320
There is a precise formula
we must follow

1034
01:04:12.400 --> 01:04:13.800
so as not to trigger the mechanism.

1035
01:04:13.960 --> 01:04:14.960
What's the formula?

1036
01:04:15.040 --> 01:04:16.120
It's quite simple.

1037
01:04:16.600 --> 01:04:19.080
Starting from the center,
use odd-numbered blocks only

1038
01:04:19.160 --> 01:04:21.441
moving forward with each step,
except for every fifth step

1039
01:04:21.480 --> 01:04:22.680
which must be a lateral move.

1040
01:04:23.040 --> 01:04:24.320
Left or right, it matters not

1041
01:04:24.400 --> 01:04:26.640
so long as the leader
and the laggard remain equidistant.

1042
01:04:26.680 --> 01:04:29.600
After which, proceed.
Again, odd-numbered blocks only.

1043
01:04:29.680 --> 01:04:32.560
However, at the midpoint
we switch to even-numbered blocks.

1044
01:04:32.640 --> 01:04:35.400
Same pattern, except now
a lateral move after the fourth step

1045
01:04:35.480 --> 01:04:36.560
until we reach the three...

1046
01:04:47.400 --> 01:04:48.400
I may have...

1047
01:04:49.080 --> 01:04:50.680
put my foot on the bridge.

1048
01:04:51.320 --> 01:04:53.320
Didn't realize that's where
it technically started.

1049
01:04:56.280 --> 01:04:58.160
So... sorry.

1050
01:05:04.000 --> 01:05:05.920
It's not very structurally sound.

1051
01:05:07.880 --> 01:05:10.040
Can't you just magic us across?

1052
01:05:11.760 --> 01:05:13.520
It's too far for telekinesis.

1053
01:05:14.640 --> 01:05:16.400
I've got some rope in my bag.

1054
01:05:16.480 --> 01:05:17.960
I could tie it to the axe.

1055
01:05:18.040 --> 01:05:20.280
Toss it across
so it sticks to the rock.

1056
01:05:20.360 --> 01:05:22.080
You know rocks are hard, right?

1057
01:05:22.160 --> 01:05:23.200
Shut up.

1058
01:05:23.840 --> 01:05:24.880
Where did you get that?

1059
01:05:26.360 --> 01:05:27.840
What, Marlamin's walking stick?

1060
01:05:27.920 --> 01:05:30.160
I swiped it from a wizard
over in the Greypeaks.

1061
01:05:30.240 --> 01:05:31.880
That's not a walking stick.

1062
01:05:33.760 --> 01:05:35.960
- It's a Hither-Thither staff.
- A what?

1063
01:05:36.040 --> 01:05:37.960
Should have a range
of around 500 yards.

1064
01:05:39.400 --> 01:05:40.400
Watch.

1065
01:05:40.600 --> 01:05:41.640
Hither.

1066
01:05:42.800 --> 01:05:43.800
Thither.

1067
01:05:45.800 --> 01:05:47.120
It works!

1068
01:05:50.680 --> 01:05:51.680
See?

1069
01:05:52.720 --> 01:05:54.480
Didn't even need the bridge!

1070
01:05:55.600 --> 01:05:56.840
I did good.

1071
01:05:58.000 --> 01:05:59.040
Good save.

1072
01:06:38.040 --> 01:06:39.440
This I give you now

1073
01:06:39.840 --> 01:06:42.520
trusting that you will
protect it with your very life.

1074
01:06:43.240 --> 01:06:44.320
I will.

1075
01:06:45.800 --> 01:06:46.880
Hold this.

1076
01:06:51.640 --> 01:06:53.200
There is evil here.

1077
01:07:04.960 --> 01:07:06.040
Are those...

1078
01:07:06.880 --> 01:07:08.240
Thayan assassins.

1079
01:07:25.120 --> 01:07:26.360
Leave them to me.

1080
01:07:50.680 --> 01:07:53.360
<i>Cothin al nepeai!</i>

1081
01:08:55.800 --> 01:08:57.400
I'm glad he's on our side.

1082
01:09:01.320 --> 01:09:02.320
We must flee.

1083
01:09:02.400 --> 01:09:03.720
Why? You killed them all.

1084
01:09:03.800 --> 01:09:06.240
'Tis no simple feat to kill that
which is already dead.

1085
01:09:15.640 --> 01:09:16.640
Quickly!

1086
01:10:03.480 --> 01:10:05.360
That's one pudgy dragon.

1087
01:10:05.440 --> 01:10:08.600
It's Themberchaud.
He must have found a new den.

1088
01:10:08.680 --> 01:10:09.920
Did he eat the last one?

1089
01:11:24.120 --> 01:11:25.120
I got you!

1090
01:11:36.000 --> 01:11:37.200
It's a dead end!

1091
01:11:38.280 --> 01:11:39.880
Simon! Up there!

1092
01:12:30.120 --> 01:12:31.160
Thanks for that.

1093
01:12:32.240 --> 01:12:33.800
You'd have done the same for me.

1094
01:12:35.640 --> 01:12:36.640
Yeah.

1095
01:12:39.000 --> 01:12:40.520
Bastard won't quit!

1096
01:12:50.960 --> 01:12:52.920
Come on! He's stuck!

1097
01:12:54.200 --> 01:12:55.200
So are we.

1098
01:13:01.680 --> 01:13:02.760
We're gonna drown!

1099
01:13:03.000 --> 01:13:04.560
Well, portal us out of here!

1100
01:13:04.640 --> 01:13:06.320
I can only portal us
to what I can see!

1101
01:13:06.400 --> 01:13:08.080
You want to go
from that wall to that wall?

1102
01:13:09.160 --> 01:13:10.360
It's salt water.

1103
01:13:11.240 --> 01:13:13.960
Simon, you remember that trick
you did in Triboar?

1104
01:13:14.040 --> 01:13:15.200
Fresh-cut grass smell?

1105
01:13:15.360 --> 01:13:17.440
No, the flame finger one.

1106
01:13:17.520 --> 01:13:19.240
- Yeah, why?
- Holga, hit him!

1107
01:13:19.440 --> 01:13:20.920
You want to make him angrier?

1108
01:13:21.200 --> 01:13:23.640
When I say so,
everybody goes underwater.

1109
01:13:23.720 --> 01:13:25.760
And that'll be your cue,
Simon, all right?

1110
01:13:26.720 --> 01:13:27.960
What are you looking at?

1111
01:13:28.160 --> 01:13:30.880
A Harper shaking off his slumber.

1112
01:13:32.160 --> 01:13:33.160
Go, Holga!

1113
01:13:37.760 --> 01:13:38.760
Again!

1114
01:13:41.960 --> 01:13:42.960
Now!

1115
01:14:19.840 --> 01:14:21.080
This is where I leave you.

1116
01:14:21.320 --> 01:14:23.400
I wish you every success
on your journey.

1117
01:14:25.680 --> 01:14:27.680
- You're not coming?
- Would that I could.

1118
01:14:27.920 --> 01:14:29.200
But this is your quest.

1119
01:14:30.080 --> 01:14:33.480
I have given you the tools.
You must utilize them.

1120
01:14:33.560 --> 01:14:35.200
Can't you utilize them for us?

1121
01:14:35.280 --> 01:14:37.840
Because you're much better
at fighting and strategy and...

1122
01:14:37.920 --> 01:14:40.200
Pretty much everything but talking.

1123
01:14:41.880 --> 01:14:43.080
Talking to you isn't great.

1124
01:14:45.720 --> 01:14:49.080
In those instances where
faith wanes and doubt waxes

1125
01:14:49.160 --> 01:14:50.576
I recall
the Tenets of the Ancients...

1126
01:14:50.600 --> 01:14:52.440
Okay. See you later.

1127
01:15:07.280 --> 01:15:08.400
There he goes.

1128
01:15:10.760 --> 01:15:12.280
Just wandering off.

1129
01:15:13.640 --> 01:15:15.800
Walks in such a straight line.

1130
01:15:17.440 --> 01:15:19.000
Wait a minute.
He's coming up on a rock.

1131
01:15:19.080 --> 01:15:21.000
Is he gonna go around?

1132
01:15:21.360 --> 01:15:22.360
Nope.

1133
01:15:22.720 --> 01:15:24.200
Right over the rock.

1134
01:15:31.520 --> 01:15:32.640
What are you mumbling?

1135
01:15:33.240 --> 01:15:35.440
I'm preparing to attune.

1136
01:15:35.520 --> 01:15:37.880
If I can't connect with it,
it'll be useless.

1137
01:15:39.360 --> 01:15:42.080
That's a lot of pressure,
given all we went through to get it.

1138
01:15:42.160 --> 01:15:43.360
Yeah, I realize that.

1139
01:15:45.760 --> 01:15:47.760
So our entire fate rests on you.

1140
01:15:49.480 --> 01:15:50.520
Come on.

1141
01:16:12.680 --> 01:16:15.680
There he is, the great Simon Aumar.

1142
01:16:16.120 --> 01:16:19.000
Sorcerer descended
from wizarding blood.

1143
01:16:19.360 --> 01:16:20.360
Who are you?

1144
01:16:20.920 --> 01:16:22.160
Don't you know me?

1145
01:16:23.960 --> 01:16:25.640
My name is Aumar too.

1146
01:16:27.440 --> 01:16:29.120
You're my great-great grandfather.

1147
01:16:32.280 --> 01:16:34.320
That's quite a helm.

1148
01:16:34.960 --> 01:16:37.120
What makes you think
you're worthy of it?

1149
01:16:38.280 --> 01:16:39.880
I believe in myself?

1150
01:16:40.320 --> 01:16:41.400
You're asking me?

1151
01:16:41.480 --> 01:16:43.240
No, I'm... I'm sure.

1152
01:16:43.720 --> 01:16:44.880
I'm a great sorcerer.

1153
01:16:45.400 --> 01:16:46.560
Are you now?

1154
01:16:47.880 --> 01:16:49.560
Funny thing about magic.

1155
01:16:50.560 --> 01:16:52.920
It chooses who may wield it.

1156
01:16:53.400 --> 01:16:55.360
And it does not suffer fools.

1157
01:16:55.560 --> 01:16:56.800
Why are you telling me this?

1158
01:16:57.120 --> 01:16:58.560
I think you know

1159
01:16:59.400 --> 01:17:00.440
Simon.

1160
01:17:04.520 --> 01:17:05.760
Did you attune with it?

1161
01:17:06.200 --> 01:17:07.240
You okay?

1162
01:17:07.880 --> 01:17:08.880
I got you.

1163
01:17:10.160 --> 01:17:11.200
What happened?

1164
01:17:11.720 --> 01:17:12.720
I...

1165
01:17:13.120 --> 01:17:14.680
- I spoke to someone.
- Yeah?

1166
01:17:15.120 --> 01:17:17.240
My great-great grandfather. He was...

1167
01:17:18.280 --> 01:17:20.200
- unhelpful.
- You spoke to him?

1168
01:17:20.880 --> 01:17:23.256
From here, it looked like the helmet
flew off the second you put it on.

1169
01:17:23.280 --> 01:17:24.920
Well, time moves differently there.

1170
01:17:25.640 --> 01:17:27.360
Okay, I'll try a different approach.

1171
01:17:27.560 --> 01:17:29.200
Great. New approach. Try it.

1172
01:17:30.760 --> 01:17:31.960
You got this. You got this.

1173
01:17:38.560 --> 01:17:40.440
You're getting better.
You didn't fly as far.

1174
01:17:40.520 --> 01:17:41.520
Stick with it.

1175
01:17:41.600 --> 01:17:43.520
We have six hours
till we leave for Neverwinter.

1176
01:17:43.680 --> 01:17:45.520
You fail, I never get my family back.

1177
01:17:45.600 --> 01:17:46.640
Brilliant.

1178
01:18:05.160 --> 01:18:07.200
I've never seen a bigger coward.

1179
01:18:07.560 --> 01:18:09.600
Coward? You're under here, too.

1180
01:18:10.280 --> 01:18:11.640
Fine. I'll handle it.

1181
01:18:11.800 --> 01:18:13.200
No, no, no.

1182
01:18:14.560 --> 01:18:15.640
I've got this.

1183
01:18:19.080 --> 01:18:20.680
And you want to be a Harper.

1184
01:18:20.760 --> 01:18:21.760
Quiet!

1185
01:18:25.880 --> 01:18:28.080
Oh, God. Damn.

1186
01:18:28.680 --> 01:18:29.680
There it is.

1187
01:18:31.320 --> 01:18:33.160
Stop trying to capture it.

1188
01:18:37.320 --> 01:18:38.760
You just have to let it go.

1189
01:18:40.320 --> 01:18:41.320
<i>Ed!</i>

1190
01:18:42.240 --> 01:18:44.560
Ed! We've got a problem.

1191
01:18:44.920 --> 01:18:46.040
I can't do it.

1192
01:18:47.120 --> 01:18:48.960
- The helmet?
- I've been at it for hours!

1193
01:18:49.040 --> 01:18:50.840
I can't get past the old bastard!

1194
01:18:50.920 --> 01:18:53.200
I said I couldn't attune.
Now I'm the prat!

1195
01:18:53.400 --> 01:18:54.600
What's the racket?

1196
01:18:54.680 --> 01:18:57.080
He's having a little trouble
with the helm.

1197
01:18:57.280 --> 01:18:59.160
Come on, Simon, just do it.

1198
01:18:59.920 --> 01:19:02.600
Yeah, okay. Yeah.
Thanks, Holga. I'll just do it.

1199
01:19:02.680 --> 01:19:04.976
This is exactly what I told you
would happen back at the tavern

1200
01:19:05.000 --> 01:19:06.080
but you wouldn't listen.

1201
01:19:06.360 --> 01:19:07.920
What do you mean, you told him?

1202
01:19:08.360 --> 01:19:10.600
He said to keep it
between us for morale.

1203
01:19:10.680 --> 01:19:11.880
- I...
- Do you know why?

1204
01:19:11.960 --> 01:19:14.520
Because he is the most
pigheaded person I've ever known!

1205
01:19:15.000 --> 01:19:17.160
You talk us into doing things
you know won't work

1206
01:19:17.240 --> 01:19:19.016
and then you blame us
when it goes pear-shaped!

1207
01:19:19.040 --> 01:19:21.400
If you can't attune,
we'll figure out a Plan B.

1208
01:19:21.480 --> 01:19:25.000
Plan B? We dug up my family. We went
to the Underdark for that helmet.

1209
01:19:25.120 --> 01:19:27.200
And you knew the whole time
that he couldn't use it?

1210
01:19:27.600 --> 01:19:29.440
You humans.
You just can't help but lie.

1211
01:19:29.520 --> 01:19:32.120
I didn't lie.
I really thought Simon could do it.

1212
01:19:32.200 --> 01:19:35.040
Guys, look. We got a couple hours
till the games begin.

1213
01:19:35.120 --> 01:19:37.280
This is what we do. We pivot.

1214
01:19:37.560 --> 01:19:39.736
Instead of dwelling on
what went wrong and who lied to whom

1215
01:19:39.760 --> 01:19:41.920
let's put our heads together
and figure out a plan!

1216
01:19:42.000 --> 01:19:43.880
I'm gonna figure out my way home.

1217
01:19:44.120 --> 01:19:45.880
I can't believe I put my faith
in any of you.

1218
01:19:45.960 --> 01:19:47.120
Yeah, I'm going too.

1219
01:19:47.440 --> 01:19:48.560
Sorry about Kira.

1220
01:19:51.320 --> 01:19:53.840
We'll find another way to get her.
Just not today.

1221
01:19:53.920 --> 01:19:56.800
It has to be today. We're not done
until my daughter's safe.

1222
01:19:56.880 --> 01:19:58.200
Aren't you sick of failing?

1223
01:19:58.280 --> 01:19:59.920
No! That's the whole point!

1224
01:20:00.000 --> 01:20:04.040
We must never stop failing, because
the minute we do, we've failed.

1225
01:20:06.320 --> 01:20:08.760
Look, none of us here
can say our lives...

1226
01:20:09.160 --> 01:20:10.760
have gone the way we had hoped for.

1227
01:20:11.480 --> 01:20:12.480
Right?

1228
01:20:12.760 --> 01:20:13.760
Holga.

1229
01:20:14.040 --> 01:20:15.920
You left your tribe to be with a man

1230
01:20:16.000 --> 01:20:19.280
who left you because you were
so upset about leaving your tribe.

1231
01:20:19.960 --> 01:20:22.200
And if you quit now, that's in stone!

1232
01:20:22.480 --> 01:20:23.800
Same with you, Simon.

1233
01:20:24.160 --> 01:20:26.960
You're a petty thief masquerading
as a pettier sorcerer.

1234
01:20:27.040 --> 01:20:28.280
You gonna go back to your show?

1235
01:20:28.320 --> 01:20:29.360
It's better than dying.

1236
01:20:29.920 --> 01:20:31.200
There's worse things than dying.

1237
01:20:31.520 --> 01:20:33.360
And, Doric, you have integrity

1238
01:20:33.440 --> 01:20:36.360
and I'm sure the last thing you want
to do is tell the Emerald Enclave

1239
01:20:36.440 --> 01:20:38.296
that you had a chance
to save them but walked away.

1240
01:20:38.320 --> 01:20:39.920
You're quick to call us failures.

1241
01:20:40.000 --> 01:20:41.600
- What about you, Ed?
- Me?

1242
01:20:42.440 --> 01:20:44.360
I'm the champion of failures!

1243
01:20:45.240 --> 01:20:48.240
I lost everything that ever mattered
to me and it was all my fault.

1244
01:20:54.200 --> 01:20:55.920
You want to know
who really killed my wife?

1245
01:20:58.880 --> 01:20:59.920
I did.

1246
01:21:01.120 --> 01:21:05.200
<i>I decided we deserved a better life
than a Harper's oath would allow us.</i>

1247
01:21:07.120 --> 01:21:09.600
<i>But I didn't know that
Red Wizards marked their treasure.</i>

1248
01:21:12.360 --> 01:21:13.800
I led them right to our door.

1249
01:21:16.600 --> 01:21:19.320
I didn't even have the good luck
to be home when they got there.

1250
01:21:21.240 --> 01:21:24.000
I failed the Harpers, I failed
my family, I failed all of you.

1251
01:21:24.160 --> 01:21:26.000
Which is exactly why I can't quit.

1252
01:21:26.120 --> 01:21:28.680
So if you'll excuse me,
I'm gonna go sit on this rock

1253
01:21:29.720 --> 01:21:30.880
and make a plan.

1254
01:21:43.320 --> 01:21:44.320
Move over.

1255
01:22:18.520 --> 01:22:20.800
I'd sit too, but there's
no more room on the rock.

1256
01:22:23.600 --> 01:22:24.680
How about this?

1257
01:22:26.000 --> 01:22:28.440
We use the Hither-Thither Staff
to get into the vault.

1258
01:22:28.520 --> 01:22:29.720
No, I've explained this.

1259
01:22:29.800 --> 01:22:31.880
You can't Hither-Thither
into a room you can't see.

1260
01:22:32.040 --> 01:22:33.920
I'm not saying that. I'm saying

1261
01:22:34.160 --> 01:22:37.960
we put the portal on something and
then sneak that thing into the vault.

1262
01:22:39.200 --> 01:22:41.240
The only thing going
in that vault is treasure.

1263
01:22:41.320 --> 01:22:43.360
So we put the portal
on some treasure.

1264
01:22:45.880 --> 01:22:48.640
Forge did say the richest men
in Baldur's Gate and Waterdeep

1265
01:22:48.720 --> 01:22:50.320
are bringing loot to the city.

1266
01:22:51.520 --> 01:22:54.360
They'll be traveling the High Road.
We could catch one of their convoys!

1267
01:22:54.400 --> 01:22:55.536
But there'll be dozens of guards.

1268
01:22:55.560 --> 01:22:57.536
Yeah, but the guards
will be guarding against people

1269
01:22:57.560 --> 01:23:00.480
taking things out of their wagon,
not putting them in!

1270
01:23:00.560 --> 01:23:01.600
Holga, I could kiss you!

1271
01:23:01.680 --> 01:23:02.680
Try it.

1272
01:23:07.080 --> 01:23:08.480
Perfect. Thank you so much.

1273
01:25:25.400 --> 01:25:29.880
What a profound joy it is
to welcome you

1274
01:25:30.120 --> 01:25:32.440
the good people of Neverwinter

1275
01:25:32.520 --> 01:25:36.560
to the resumption
of the High Sun Games!

1276
01:25:40.040 --> 01:25:43.480
I guarantee that you are in
for the most riveting spectacle

1277
01:25:43.560 --> 01:25:45.280
on all the Sword Coast.

1278
01:25:45.720 --> 01:25:47.800
The rules are very simple:

1279
01:25:48.040 --> 01:25:51.960
Five harrowing challenges.
Five teams of champions.

1280
01:25:52.160 --> 01:25:55.240
Whoever survives
to reach the Cage of Sanctuary

1281
01:25:55.320 --> 01:25:57.760
moves on to the next stage.

1282
01:25:58.680 --> 01:25:59.680
One thing:

1283
01:26:00.080 --> 01:26:04.880
I do urge you, please do not leave
the arena till the close of the games

1284
01:26:04.960 --> 01:26:07.440
as there will be a wonderful gift

1285
01:26:07.800 --> 01:26:10.600
for each and every one of you!

1286
01:26:15.800 --> 01:26:16.880
All right, take me down.

1287
01:26:17.080 --> 01:26:19.320
This is absurdly high.
It's not what we discussed.

1288
01:26:32.920 --> 01:26:34.840
- Oh, no.
- What happened?

1289
01:26:34.920 --> 01:26:37.200
It's facing the floor.
Why would they store it that way?

1290
01:26:44.040 --> 01:26:45.616
- Damn it.
- Why does nothing go our way?

1291
01:26:45.640 --> 01:26:47.440
Let me try. Maybe I can make a gap.

1292
01:26:48.920 --> 01:26:50.120
The games have started.

1293
01:26:51.320 --> 01:26:52.600
We're going to Plan C.

1294
01:26:52.880 --> 01:26:54.480
Oh, bollocks. What's Plan C?

1295
01:26:54.560 --> 01:26:56.800
Plan C is we go back to Plan A.

1296
01:26:57.400 --> 01:26:58.456
You're gonna attune to the helmet.

1297
01:26:58.480 --> 01:27:00.000
Why don't you just call it Plan A?

1298
01:27:00.080 --> 01:27:01.120
Plan A has a stink on it.

1299
01:27:01.200 --> 01:27:03.040
You know damn well
I can't attune to the thing.

1300
01:27:03.080 --> 01:27:04.240
That's not true!

1301
01:27:04.320 --> 01:27:06.560
You couldn't attune to it.
Look at me. Look at me!

1302
01:27:07.600 --> 01:27:09.120
Do you remember
that job in Loudwater?

1303
01:27:09.440 --> 01:27:12.560
You couldn't spider climb
until Jolym sicced his dog on you.

1304
01:27:12.760 --> 01:27:14.600
And when we robbed
the spear of Aoth Fezim

1305
01:27:14.680 --> 01:27:17.400
your stoneskin spell failed
until the arrows were inches away.

1306
01:27:17.480 --> 01:27:21.160
Even in Triboar, you flipped
the gravity of a whole theater!

1307
01:27:21.560 --> 01:27:22.600
You did?

1308
01:27:23.760 --> 01:27:25.320
By accident. It was wild magic

1309
01:27:25.400 --> 01:27:26.776
and that only happened
because they were gonna kill me.

1310
01:27:26.800 --> 01:27:27.920
Exactly!

1311
01:27:28.960 --> 01:27:33.360
Look. You are at your strongest when
you think you're at your weakest.

1312
01:27:33.680 --> 01:27:34.680
But you deliver.

1313
01:27:36.720 --> 01:27:39.200
You're gonna get
into that vault, okay?

1314
01:27:39.600 --> 01:27:40.800
Not because you can...

1315
01:27:42.840 --> 01:27:44.000
but because you must.

1316
01:27:45.200 --> 01:27:46.560
I'm gonna keep chipping away.

1317
01:27:46.960 --> 01:27:49.536
If I can get a quarter inch, I'll be
able to squeeze through as a worm.

1318
01:27:49.560 --> 01:27:50.560
As a worm!

1319
01:27:50.960 --> 01:27:54.480
As a worm, perfect. You see this?
Now we have a Plan D if Plan C fails.

1320
01:27:54.560 --> 01:27:56.280
Isn't Plan D just Plan B again?

1321
01:27:56.360 --> 01:27:57.560
Plan B has a stink too.

1322
01:27:57.640 --> 01:27:58.800
It all stinks.

1323
01:27:59.360 --> 01:28:01.720
Here. Use this to keep in contact.

1324
01:28:02.800 --> 01:28:04.440
Well, this is a rock.

1325
01:28:04.520 --> 01:28:07.160
Actually it is a sending stone.

1326
01:28:07.640 --> 01:28:09.120
But they'll only work for an hour.

1327
01:28:09.800 --> 01:28:10.880
Clever.

1328
01:28:13.400 --> 01:28:14.920
So how we gonna get in there?

1329
01:28:15.080 --> 01:28:16.880
Easy. We just create a distraction.

1330
01:28:18.080 --> 01:28:20.000
I got a good feeling about Plan C.

1331
01:28:33.800 --> 01:28:35.080
What's your business here?

1332
01:28:35.960 --> 01:28:37.880
<i>When the battle is over</i>

1333
01:28:37.960 --> 01:28:39.600
<i>Friends become lovers</i>

1334
01:28:39.680 --> 01:28:42.720
<i>Sons embrace mothers,
brothers and dads</i>

1335
01:28:42.800 --> 01:28:44.960
<i>Where once were contenders</i>

1336
01:28:45.040 --> 01:28:46.720
<i>Now are befrienders</i>

1337
01:28:46.920 --> 01:28:50.080
<i>Oh, let's celebrate lasses and lads</i>

1338
01:28:50.160 --> 01:28:52.200
<i>Where once were contenders</i>

1339
01:28:52.280 --> 01:28:53.640
<i>Now are befrienders</i>

1340
01:28:53.720 --> 01:28:55.480
<i>Let's celebrate lasses</i>

1341
01:28:55.560 --> 01:28:57.040
<i>Celebrate lasses</i>

1342
01:28:57.120 --> 01:28:59.960
<i>Celebrate lasses</i>

1343
01:29:00.040 --> 01:29:01.376
What's going on?
You're messing up my song!

1344
01:29:01.400 --> 01:29:02.400
My foot is stuck.

1345
01:29:02.600 --> 01:29:04.000
Concentrate, Simon.

1346
01:29:04.360 --> 01:29:08.160
<i>Brate...</i>

1347
01:29:08.240 --> 01:29:09.600
What madness is this?

1348
01:29:09.680 --> 01:29:14.760
<i>Brate...</i>

1349
01:29:14.920 --> 01:29:17.120
I think they're starting
to get suspicious.

1350
01:29:20.160 --> 01:29:21.160
Nine hells.

1351
01:29:22.680 --> 01:29:25.520
- There! Interlopers!
- Come on!

1352
01:29:32.360 --> 01:29:33.800
Kira's room should be up there.

1353
01:29:34.080 --> 01:29:36.720
Find the vault
and we'll meet you. Go!

1354
01:29:36.800 --> 01:29:37.800
Halt!

1355
01:29:45.040 --> 01:29:46.040
There she is!

1356
01:29:46.480 --> 01:29:48.640
I'll hold them. Find the vault.

1357
01:29:48.720 --> 01:29:50.640
- You sure I can't help?
- I'm certain.

1358
01:29:51.200 --> 01:29:53.240
- You don't have to be so certain.
- Get her!

1359
01:30:26.920 --> 01:30:29.360
I'm with the Absolution Council.
They've just gone up.

1360
01:31:10.680 --> 01:31:11.680
Open up!

1361
01:31:11.880 --> 01:31:12.880
Just a minute!

1362
01:31:32.680 --> 01:31:33.880
I don't mind that.

1363
01:31:37.000 --> 01:31:39.480
Okay, you can do this.
Relax. No rush.

1364
01:31:40.160 --> 01:31:41.160
There he is!

1365
01:31:41.360 --> 01:31:42.400
Put it down!

1366
01:31:45.760 --> 01:31:47.680
Look who's back.
The would-be sorcerer.

1367
01:31:47.760 --> 01:31:49.120
I don't have time for this!

1368
01:31:49.320 --> 01:31:51.080
Yet I have all the time there is.

1369
01:31:51.160 --> 01:31:53.520
You don't get it.
We're going to die if I don't attune!

1370
01:31:53.640 --> 01:31:56.560
So you die a fool.
It's better than to live as one.

1371
01:31:56.640 --> 01:31:58.360
That's enough! You don't know me.

1372
01:31:58.560 --> 01:32:01.200
I know you're a stain
on your family name!

1373
01:32:01.280 --> 01:32:03.160
To hell with my name! Let me attune!

1374
01:32:03.240 --> 01:32:04.440
Not while I live.

1375
01:32:04.520 --> 01:32:05.560
You don't live!

1376
01:32:05.680 --> 01:32:07.840
You had your time. Now it's my turn.

1377
01:32:07.920 --> 01:32:09.040
I won't allow it.

1378
01:32:09.120 --> 01:32:10.120
I don't care!

1379
01:32:12.280 --> 01:32:13.280
Sorry.

1380
01:32:17.520 --> 01:32:18.680
Took you long enough.

1381
01:32:34.720 --> 01:32:35.720
Simon!

1382
01:32:36.920 --> 01:32:37.960
<i>Simon, was that you?</i>

1383
01:32:38.280 --> 01:32:39.920
It was! I did it!

1384
01:32:40.240 --> 01:32:41.240
Well done.

1385
01:32:42.480 --> 01:32:44.200
I guess it was just
me holding me back.

1386
01:32:44.280 --> 01:32:45.720
That's what I've been saying!

1387
01:32:54.160 --> 01:32:55.440
I made it inside the vault.

1388
01:32:55.800 --> 01:32:56.800
So did we.

1389
01:32:57.960 --> 01:32:59.240
There's nothing here.

1390
01:32:59.640 --> 01:33:02.280
<i>What do you mean?
It's all here. Where are you?</i>

1391
01:33:02.360 --> 01:33:03.360
Where are you?

1392
01:33:04.120 --> 01:33:05.560
I think I'm under the arena.

1393
01:33:07.400 --> 01:33:08.400
Forge.

1394
01:33:08.480 --> 01:33:09.520
This one here.

1395
01:33:27.160 --> 01:33:28.520
That's not good.

1396
01:33:36.800 --> 01:33:38.800
Simon! Doric! You there?

1397
01:33:38.880 --> 01:33:40.000
What are you doing here?

1398
01:33:41.160 --> 01:33:42.160
Kir!

1399
01:33:44.320 --> 01:33:45.560
I came for you.

1400
01:33:45.880 --> 01:33:46.920
We have to go.

1401
01:33:47.880 --> 01:33:48.880
You left me.

1402
01:33:49.360 --> 01:33:53.360
No. No, I know you think
I'm a liar and a bad father, but...

1403
01:33:57.480 --> 01:33:58.800
I am a bad father.

1404
01:34:02.240 --> 01:34:03.680
And I did leave you.

1405
01:34:04.640 --> 01:34:06.360
And I wasn't trying
to bring your mom back.

1406
01:34:06.440 --> 01:34:07.640
I was trying to...

1407
01:34:08.600 --> 01:34:10.000
bring my wife back.

1408
01:34:11.320 --> 01:34:14.200
Which maybe if you had
gotten a chance to know her

1409
01:34:15.280 --> 01:34:17.760
and love her like I did,
you'd understand.

1410
01:34:17.880 --> 01:34:19.680
But if you come with me now

1411
01:34:20.480 --> 01:34:22.000
you can have that chance.

1412
01:34:44.000 --> 01:34:46.680
You'd think you'd be able to
distinguish between your own daughter

1413
01:34:46.760 --> 01:34:48.120
and a 300-year-old wizard.

1414
01:34:48.760 --> 01:34:49.880
Don't worry, Kira's safe.

1415
01:34:49.960 --> 01:34:51.800
Unlike me, she had no idea
you were coming.

1416
01:34:51.880 --> 01:34:54.760
I don't think she knows
how tenacious you've become.

1417
01:34:56.920 --> 01:34:57.920
Look, Ed...

1418
01:35:01.240 --> 01:35:03.560
I'm really sorry about
the way things have worked out.

1419
01:35:04.560 --> 01:35:06.760
But I think if you were truly honest

1420
01:35:07.040 --> 01:35:09.840
you'd have to admit
I can give Kira a better life.

1421
01:35:10.800 --> 01:35:12.520
I hope you can take
comfort in knowing

1422
01:35:12.600 --> 01:35:14.200
that she's with
the father she deserves.

1423
01:35:15.200 --> 01:35:18.920
And now I'm in a pickle
because I don't want to see you die.

1424
01:35:20.520 --> 01:35:23.680
Which is why
I'm gonna leave the room.

1425
01:35:26.760 --> 01:35:27.760
What?

1426
01:35:35.800 --> 01:35:38.081
If you're gonna kill us,
at least let us die with dignity.

1427
01:35:38.400 --> 01:35:39.400
How do you mean?

1428
01:35:39.480 --> 01:35:42.320
Put us in the High Sun Games.
Give us a fighting chance.

1429
01:35:42.520 --> 01:35:44.960
That's not a chance.
It's not a chance at all.

1430
01:35:45.040 --> 01:35:47.600
I mean, even if you were
to somehow survive the tournament

1431
01:35:47.680 --> 01:35:48.680
Sofina's gonna...

1432
01:35:52.200 --> 01:35:56.160
It would be much, much better for you
to die here than to go to the games.

1433
01:35:56.240 --> 01:35:57.240
No.

1434
01:35:57.320 --> 01:36:01.320
They defeated your men and mine.
Let them fight in the arena.

1435
01:36:02.080 --> 01:36:03.800
They deserve that much.

1436
01:36:10.680 --> 01:36:11.720
Bad day.

1437
01:36:13.200 --> 01:36:14.640
You might want to go back to sleep.

1438
01:36:15.200 --> 01:36:16.200
Are we...

1439
01:36:16.280 --> 01:36:17.280
In the arena.

1440
01:36:19.800 --> 01:36:22.240
This dummy talked Forge
into putting us in the games.

1441
01:36:22.320 --> 01:36:24.000
Dummy? I saved our lives!

1442
01:36:24.080 --> 01:36:25.936
And I got us right above
where Doric said the treasure was.

1443
01:36:25.960 --> 01:36:28.440
Isn't it a little suspect
that Sofina would agree to this?

1444
01:36:28.520 --> 01:36:30.360
Yeah, she's definitely
planned something.

1445
01:36:31.480 --> 01:36:32.920
Where under the arena were you?

1446
01:36:34.000 --> 01:36:35.000
Do you remember?

1447
01:36:35.920 --> 01:36:36.960
Not sure.

1448
01:36:38.320 --> 01:36:39.560
There was a dock down there.

1449
01:36:40.120 --> 01:36:42.560
I saw guards loading
everything onto a ship.

1450
01:36:44.720 --> 01:36:45.720
A ship.

1451
01:36:46.920 --> 01:36:48.560
Forge wasn't hiding
the loot from us.

1452
01:36:48.680 --> 01:36:50.120
He was stealing it for himself.

1453
01:36:50.200 --> 01:36:51.480
He never cared about being Lord.

1454
01:36:51.520 --> 01:36:53.200
That just gave him
access to the vault.

1455
01:36:53.480 --> 01:36:56.000
He must have brought back the games
so the take would be bigger.

1456
01:36:57.280 --> 01:36:58.400
What about Kira?

1457
01:36:59.680 --> 01:37:01.776
He won't leave her behind.
We have to get to that boat.

1458
01:37:01.800 --> 01:37:03.720
I don't understand.
If Forge is leaving

1459
01:37:03.800 --> 01:37:05.360
what does Sofina get out of this?

1460
01:37:13.760 --> 01:37:15.360
Maybe I can get us out of here.

1461
01:37:18.680 --> 01:37:20.080
Magic suppression cuff.

1462
01:37:20.600 --> 01:37:21.680
They put one on me too.

1463
01:37:22.000 --> 01:37:23.680
And just when
you were getting good at it.

1464
01:38:22.000 --> 01:38:23.800
So we just go through the maze?

1465
01:38:24.000 --> 01:38:25.520
I guess till we reach the cage?

1466
01:38:31.760 --> 01:38:32.760
Run!

1467
01:38:47.280 --> 01:38:48.280
Follow me!

1468
01:39:41.920 --> 01:39:42.920
Thanks.

1469
01:39:45.400 --> 01:39:46.400
Where are the others?

1470
01:39:46.480 --> 01:39:47.800
Come on, this way.

1471
01:39:52.960 --> 01:39:55.200
Have you tried Displacer Beast meat?

1472
01:39:55.720 --> 01:39:57.560
No. It's too gamey for me.

1473
01:39:59.520 --> 01:40:00.880
The ship is ready, sir.

1474
01:40:06.880 --> 01:40:09.760
It seems my ship is ready, so...

1475
01:40:10.720 --> 01:40:12.920
Kira and I will be taking our leave.

1476
01:40:15.120 --> 01:40:16.400
I do hope that

1477
01:40:16.480 --> 01:40:19.080
our collaboration has been
as gratifying for you

1478
01:40:19.160 --> 01:40:20.880
- as it has for...
- Get out of my city.

1479
01:40:21.480 --> 01:40:22.480
Right.

1480
01:40:26.760 --> 01:40:27.760
Get out of the way!

1481
01:40:28.760 --> 01:40:29.760
It's burning!

1482
01:40:35.480 --> 01:40:37.120
Another minute,
I would have lost my hand.

1483
01:40:37.200 --> 01:40:38.720
Yeah, but look what you did lose.

1484
01:40:39.520 --> 01:40:40.520
Come on.

1485
01:40:40.600 --> 01:40:42.400
Doric? Doric!

1486
01:40:42.480 --> 01:40:44.320
There must be a way
to get out of the arena.

1487
01:41:01.200 --> 01:41:02.200
Come on! Come on!

1488
01:41:15.640 --> 01:41:16.640
No.

1489
01:41:17.400 --> 01:41:19.480
- No, this isn't the way out.
- Yes, it is.

1490
01:41:19.560 --> 01:41:21.696
If we survive this, there'll be
another challenge and another

1491
01:41:21.720 --> 01:41:24.000
until every last person
in that cage is dead.

1492
01:41:24.360 --> 01:41:25.720
We have to find a work-around.

1493
01:41:28.000 --> 01:41:29.760
I've got an idea. Follow me.

1494
01:41:32.000 --> 01:41:33.680
Hey! What's your idea?

1495
01:41:40.800 --> 01:41:42.480
When we hear the gong, we jump in.

1496
01:41:43.120 --> 01:41:44.160
Into this thing?

1497
01:41:44.240 --> 01:41:45.800
You want to end up like that guy?

1498
01:41:45.880 --> 01:41:47.800
We will only be inside
for a few seconds.

1499
01:41:51.600 --> 01:41:53.360
If we're all inside,
who's gonna pull us out?

1500
01:41:53.440 --> 01:41:55.320
- I will, trust me.
- Always.

1501
01:41:55.880 --> 01:41:56.880
Hold.

1502
01:42:00.240 --> 01:42:01.240
Hold.

1503
01:42:03.080 --> 01:42:04.080
Hold!

1504
01:42:05.360 --> 01:42:06.360
Now!

1505
01:42:38.560 --> 01:42:40.200
Damn it! That stings!

1506
01:42:52.120 --> 01:42:53.160
We gotta move.

1507
01:43:01.040 --> 01:43:02.040
I've been here.

1508
01:43:02.800 --> 01:43:03.880
Our gear.

1509
01:43:07.200 --> 01:43:09.360
Simon. Try these on your cuff.

1510
01:43:11.800 --> 01:43:12.880
Come with me.

1511
01:43:14.680 --> 01:43:16.200
Quite a second date, yeah?

